<SLUG> BC-AP-Weekly News Calendar,0538 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Saturday, June 13:
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Queensland, Australia _ State election, testing the anti-Asian
immigration, anti-gun control appeal of Pauline Hanson's One Nation
Party against the mainstream Labor Party and conservative
Coalition.
	   Copenhagen, Denmark _ U.S. Defense Secretary William Cohen on
one-day visit to Denmark (tentative).
	   Saint-Denis, France _ World Cup. Through July 12.
	   Israel, Egypt _ Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer
visits to talk about Mideast peace issues and trade promotion. In
Israel, he is also expected to discuss the bridge collapse at the
Maccabiah Games that killed four Jewish Australian athletes last
year. Through June 14.
 &UR; Sunday, June 14:
	   Korsoer, Denmark _ The Storebaelt bridge, linking the islands of
Zealand, where Copenhagen sits, to Funen, already linked to the
European continent, opens for car traffic.
	   Turin, Italy _ End of two-month display of Shroud of Turin. It
will go on display again in year 2000.
	   Sydney, Australia _ Hong Kong's new chief executive Tung Chee
Hwa visits to promote Hong Kong as a stable, reliable trade
partner. Through June 16.
 &UR; Monday, June 15:
	   Cardiff, Wales _ Start of two-day European Union summit.
	   Kingstown, St. Vincent _ General elections. Opposition parties
hope to seize on a 45 percent unemployment rate to unseat Prime
Minister Sir James Mitchell, who has governed St. Vincent and the
Grenadines since 1984.
	   Rome _ Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer joins other
national delegates to discuss establishment of an ``International
Criminal Court'' to try crimes against humanity. Will also discuss
trade links between Italy and Australia. Through June 18.
 &UR; Tuesday, June 16:
	   Vatican City _ U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan meets Pope John
Paul II.
	   Rome _ South Africa's President Nelson Mandela visits. Through
June 18.
	   Tokyo _ Ministry of International Trade and Industry releases
white paper on trade.
 &UR; Wednesday, June 17:
	   Wellington, New Zealand _ Hong Kong's new chief executive Tung
Chee Hwa visits to promote Hong Kong as a stable, reliable trade
partner. Through June 18.
 &UR; Thursday, June 18:
	   Port-au-Prince, Haiti _ Dominican President Leonel Fernandez on
first official visit by a Dominican leader to Haiti, a conciliatory
visit to the country that twice invaded the Dominican Republic.
	   Bucharest, Romania _ Bucharest state court resumes hearing
witness in the case of British priest Michael Taylor charged with
having sexual relations with two minors.
	   Budapest, Hungary _ First session of newly elected parliament.
 &UR; Friday, June 19:
	   Prague, Czech Republic _ Early elections. Through June 20.
	   Helsinki, Finland _ Exiled Tibetan spiritual leader Dalai Lama
visits. Through June 21.
	   Vienna, Austria _ Pope John Paul II visits. Through June 21.
	   Bangkok, Thailand _ Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer
visits to discuss Asian regional economic crisis and Thailand's
adoption of IMF reforms. Through June 20.
 &UR; Saturday, June 20:
	   No major events added.
 &UR; Sunday, June 21:
	   No major events added.
</TEXT>
