<HEADLINE>
Connors defeats Mayer at BTI Champions
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with Connors win. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   RALEIGH, North Carolina (AP) _ Top-seeded Jimmy Connors defeated
Gene Mayer 6-3, 6-2 Thursday in the quarterfinals of the dlrs
150,000 BTI Champions senior tennis tournament at the Raleigh
Racquet Club.
	   The victory was Connors' third in three meetings against fellow
American Mayer, who was once ranked as high as fourth in the world.
	   ``It's challenging to play Gene because he has such an all-court
game,'' Connors said. ``He disguises his shots well and he's so
strong off both sides that sometimes I feel like I've got to go for
a little bit too much.''
	   The win advanced Connors to Saturday's semifinals where he will
meet the winner of Friday's match between John Lloyd and Mansour
Bahrami of France.
	   In a first-round match Thursday, Mel Purcell trounced fellow
American Tim Wilkison 6-1, 6-2 and Bahrami beat Australia's John
Fitzgerald 3-6, 7-5, 10-6.
	   Purcell's win advanced him to the quarterfinals against
second-seeded Johan Kriek.
	   The BTI Champions is the second event on the 1998-1999 Nuveen
Tour.
</TEXT>
