<HEADLINE>
Report: German man dies of heart attack while watching World Cup
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ A German resident of Thailand died of a
heart attack while watching World Cup soccer matches, the Bangkok
Post reported Friday.
	   Heinz Erich Deutsch, 62, was found dead by his Thai wife,
Bang-orn Chiang-in, in their home in Chonburi, just south of
Bangkok.
	   She said she believed he had suffered a heart attack while
watching the opening matches, according to the Post.
	   Deutsch's body was taken to a hospital in nearby Pattaya for an
autopsy, although police do not suspect foul play, the Post said. 	   
</TEXT>
