<HEADLINE>
Canada 1, USA 0
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TUCSON, Arizona (AP) _ Canada's Brent Crowther shut out the
United States 1-0 Tuesday night in the second game of their
five-game baseball series.
	   Crowther scattered eight hits in handing the Americans their
first loss in six games. USA beat Canada 20-3 Wednesday night after
sweeping a four-game series with Mexico.
	   Crowther went the route while striking out two batters, walking
none and retiring 20 of the last 25 batters he faced.
	   Dominic Campeau scored Canada's run on a second-inning single by
Kyle Brunen.
	   Matt Smith of the United States suffered the loss.
