<SLUG> BC-Sports-Cricket-Sri Lanka-New Zealand </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ranatunga and Tillekeratne rescue Sri Lanka
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With BC-Sports-Cricket-Sri Lanka-New Zealand-Scoreboard &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos planned &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) _ Sri Lanka went to lunch at 88 for four
wickets, a lead of 101 runs on day three of the third and final
cricket Test at the Sinhalese Sports Club on Friday.
	   At the wicket were skipper Arjuna Ranatunga on 41 and Hashan
Tillekeratne on 17. The pair came together with Sri Lanka tottering
on 36 for four wickets, and have so far put on 52 to rebuild the
inning.
	   Sri Lanka started the day disastrously, losing star opener
Sanath Jayasuriya for eight, caught behind off paceman Chris
Cairns.
	   Left-arm spinner Daniel Vettori then picked up three quick
wickets, those of Marvan Atapattu (5), Aravinda de Silva (3), and
Mahela Jayawardena (11).
	   Atapattu was beaten by a ball which kept low, de Silva was
caught at mid-off by Nathan Astle, and Mathew Horne held on to a
brilliant catch at mid-wicket to dismiss Jayawardena. Vettori has
taken three wickets for 16 runs off 12 overs.
	   With eight sessions to go, either side could win and take the
series, which is tied 1-1.
	   (cd/ne)
</TEXT>
