<HEADLINE>
Famed perfumer wounded in attack by armed gang
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ Up to a dozen masked men attacked the home of
world-renowned perfumer Jean-Paul Guerlain early Friday, shooting
him in the thigh and making off with millions of francs in silver,
jewels and money, French radio reported.
	   An employee was shot in the chest, according to France Info
radio.
	   According to several accounts, the gang, armed with hunting
rifles and other weapons, broke into Guerlain's home in the
Yvelines region west of Paris, about 3 a.m. After the shootout,
they made off with their booty in a large car.
	   The account could not be immediately confirmed. Further
information was not immediately available.
	   On Thursday night, Guerlain presented his new perfume,
``Guerlinade,'' at a show on the Champs-Elysees, the famed Paris
avenue.
