<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Indonesia-Suharto-Lawyers </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Indonesia's ex-President hires foreign lawyers: reports
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) _ Former President Suharto has hired
foreign lawyers to handle allegations of corruption during his
32-year rule, news reports said Friday.
	   Attorney General Sudjono Atmonegoro was quoted as saying his
office has received a letter from the lawyers stating that they now
were representing Suharto, who resigned last month.
	   Sudjono, however, refused to identify the foreign lawyers's
names or nationality, the daily Kompas newspaper said.
	   Suharto stepped down on May 21, after riots and violent protests
left at least 1,188 dead in Jakarta and other cities.
	   Since then, critics have called for Suharto to face trial for
corruption and abuse of power. They also want the state to seize
billions of dollars amassed by his family and use it to help solve
nation's acute economic problems.
	   Justice Minister Muladi said Suharto has the right to hire
foreign lawyers, but they have to work with Indonesian law firms.
	   Otherwise, the foreign lawyers can only act as consultants,
Muladi was quoted as saying by Kompas. Other newspapers also
carried reports saying that Suharto had hired a foreign-based legal
team.
</TEXT>
