<HEADLINE>
Precede PARIS
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Famed perfumer wounded in attack by armed gang &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with police confirm attack; report Guerlain in
critical condition; ADDS background &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   VERSAILLES, France _ About 10 masked men attacked the home of
world-renowned perfumer Jean-Paul Guerlain early Friday, shooting
him in the thigh and making off with millions of francs worth of
jewels and money, police said.
	   Guerlain and an employee shot in the chest in the attack were
hospitalized in the Yvelines region west of Paris where Guerlain's
home is located.
	   Police sources reported that Guerlain was in critical condition,
with a vital artery apparently injured. The information could not
be immediately confirmed.
	   According to accounts on French radio, the gang, armed with
hunting rifles and other weapons, broke into Guerlain's home,
called ``Mesnuls,'' near Montfort-l'Amaury, about 3 a.m. After the
shootout, they made off with their booty in a large car.
	   Further information was not immediately available.
	   On Thursday night, Guerlain presented his new perfume,
``Guerlinade,'' at a show on the Champs-Elysees, the famed Paris
avenue.
	   Guerlain is the great grandson of the founder of the prestigious
perfume and cosmetics house created in 1828.
	   Guerlain has been run by the world's No. 1 luxury group LMVH --
Louis Vuitton Moet-Henessy -- since 1994.
	   (eg-parf)
