<HEADLINE>
Fire 5, Clash 2
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CHICAGO (AP) _ Peter Nowak scored twice as the Chicago Fire beat
the San Jose Clash 5-2 on Thursday night, extending the Major
League Soccer expansion team's winning streak to six games.
	   Nowak, the team's leading scorer with six goals and seven
assists, scored in the 33rd and 49th minutes. Ante Razov, Rich
Kotschau and Josh Wolff also scored for the Fire (8-5).
	   Francisco Uribe and Ronald Cerritos scored late goals for San
Jose (5-10), ending Fire goaltender Zach Thornton's shutout string
at 253 minutes. Thornton has a league-high four shutouts.
	   Uribe made his Clash debut as a second-half substitute. His goal
in the 76th minute ended San Jose's scoreless streak at 315
minutes.
</TEXT>
