<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Jordan-Shooting </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Family of 11 shot to death in a mysterious crime
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AMMAN, Jordan (AP) _ Assailants stormed the house of a school
bus driver, killing him and 11 relatives in a shooting that shook a
country boasting of its security in a volatile region.
	   The shooting took place before dawn Thursday in Banayat, a
village 20 kilometers (12 miles) northwest of Amman. The gunmen
killed Amin Qashash, 50, his unidentified wife, four children, a
son-in-law and four grandchildren, officials said Friday.
	   Investigators blamed the shooting on ``either a personal feud or
financial,'' an official said on customary condition of anonymity.
	   The gunmen dragged the family into the basement of their
two-story house, where they shot them to death. The gunmen then
built a brick door to hide the entry to the basement, another
official said, also on condition of anonymity.
	   Jordan's reputation for safety and stability has been shaken
recently by a series of shootings and bombings.
 &UR; jjh-as
