<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-France-Guerlain Attacked, 2nd Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Famed perfumer wounded in attack by armed gang
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with perfume house president saying Guerlain
conscious, talking, further quotes; At least two others injured,
one critically; RESTORES AP logo &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   VERSAILLES, France (AP) _ About 10 masked men attacked the home
of world-renowned perfumer Jean-Paul Guerlain early Friday,
shooting Guerlain in the thigh and making off with millions of
francs in jewels and money, police said.
	   At least two other employees were also injured when gunfire
erupted as the gang briefly held the entire household hostage,
according to the president of the Guerlain perfume and cosmetics
house, Thibault Ponroy.
	   One of the employees, shot in the stomach, was in critical
condition, Ponroy told The Associated Press. Another was slightly
injured.
	   Ponroy said that Guerlain was operated on Friday morning and was
conscious and chatting with him by telephone hours later. He denied
earlier reports that Guerlain was in critical condition.
	   There was no clear information on the others injured in the
attack at Guerlain's home in the Yvelines region, west of Paris.
	   Exactly how the attack occurred was not immediately clear.
	   Ponroy was quoted by LCI television station as saying that
apparently the armed gang took the entire household hostage in the
attack, which occurred between midnight and 3 a.m.
	   ``In circumstances I am unaware of, a shootout broke out,''
Ponroy said on LCI.
	   Guerlain ``is out of danger,'' Ponroy said. ``He was
complaining. When Jean-Paul complains, he's doing well.''
	   According to French radio, the gang, armed with hunting rifles
and other weapons, made off with their booty in a large car.
	   Police said they stole money and various valuables worth
millions of francs.
	   Guerlain's home, called ``Mesnuls,'' is located near
Montfort-l'Amaury in the Yvelines.
	   On Thursday night, Guerlain presented his new perfume,
``Guerlinade,'' at a show on the Champs-Elysees, the famed Paris
avenue.
	   Guerlain is the great grandson of the founder of the prestigious
perfume and cosmetics house created in 1828.
	   Guerlain has been run by the world's No. 1 luxury group LMVH --
Louis Vuitton Moet-Henessy -- since 1994.
	   (eg-parf)
</TEXT>
