<HEADLINE>
McGuire stays on top in Suntory Ladies Open
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KOBE, Japan (AP) _ Marnie McGuire shot a 1-under-par 71 Friday
to stay ahead with a two-stroke lead midway through the 50 million
yen (dlrs 352,000) Suntory Ladies Open.
	   The 29-year-old New Zealander, winner of four tournaments on the
Japan tour, birdied the last three holes in a round of five birdies
and four bogeys for a 5-under 139 total. She had a one-stroke lead
overnight.
	   ``I was putting well but had a poor iron play today,'' said
McGuire, in contention for her first title in Japan since winning
the 1996 Mitsubishi Cup. ``I'll just try to play without the sense
of urgency to win.''
	   Veteran Hiromi Takamura fired the day's best round of 68 and
shared second place at 141 with Keiko Suzuki, who shot a 72.
	   Lee Young-me and her South Korean compatriot Kim Ae-sook shot
71s to share fourth at 142 with Nayoko Yoshikawa and four others.
	   Lee and Kim are seeking their second victory of the season,
while Yoshikawa is aiming at her first title for the season and
30th overall.
