<HEADLINE>
Gas explosion at nursery injures 34 children and teachers
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ A propane gas explosion at a nursery school on the
northern Japanese island of Hokkaido on Friday injured at least 32
children and two teachers, police said.
	   The victims were rushed to a nearby hospital. Most of them
suffered only slight burns on their hands and legs, but five of
them, including three children, were hospitalized, Hokkaido
Prefectural Police said.
	   The cause of the blast _ at the private Higashioka Nursery
School in Shibetsu, about 1,000 kilometers (620 miles) northeast of
Tokyo _ was being investigated.
	   The explosion also caused a small fire, while the school
building was badly damaged, local firefighters said.
