<SLUG> BC-Sports-Golf-Sapporo Tokyu </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Franco, Yoneyama share lead in Sapporo Tokyu Open
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SAPPORO, Japan (AP) _ Carlos Franco and Tsuyoshi Yoneyama shot
4-under-par 68s Friday and stayed on top with a one-stroke lead
after two rounds in the 100 million yen (dlrs 704,000) Sapporo
Tokyu Open.
	   Franco of Paraguay and Yoneyama were tied at 11-under 133, one
shot ahead of their overnight co-leader Toru Suzuki, who fired a
69.
	   Franco is seeking his third victory this season and sixth
overall on the Japan tour.
	   Yoshimitsu Fukuzawa had a 68 for 135, followed by American David
Ishii, David Smail of New Zealand, Australian Stewart Ginn and two
others who shared fifth at 136.
 &UR; (kph)
</TEXT>
