<SLUG> BC-India-Greenpeace, 3rd Ld,0137 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Greenpeace floats ``anti-nuclear'' balloon near Indian monument
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with protesters released in 2nd graf. &QL; 
 &UR; With India-Pakistan-Nuclear &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos AGR101-102 &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   AGRA, India (AP) _ Greenpeace protesters chose India's most
recognizable monument _ the Taj Mahal _ as the site of a protest
Friday, floating an Earth-shaped hot air balloon draped with
anti-nuclear banners about 200 meters (yards) from the 345-year-old
tomb.
	   Greenpeace spokeswoman Luisa Colasimone said about 30 soldiers
surrounded the balloon when it touched down after the early morning
protest in a field across a river from the Taj Mahal. She said four
protesters were detained for questioning, then released a few hours
later without being charged.
