</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Bosnia-Car Bomb </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Car bomb kills Bosnian Croat policeman, injures his Muslim
</HEADLINE>
colleague &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   SARAJEVO, Bosnia-Herzegovina (AP) _ A Bosnian Croat policeman
was killed and his Muslim colleague was injured when a bomb
exploded under their vehicle, local police and U.N. officials said
Friday.
	   The blast occurred Friday morning near the central Bosnian town
of Travnik, and it was not known who was behind it, officials said.
	   Liam McDowall, a U.N. spokesman, said both policemen were in a
private vehicle off duty when the attack happened. He said local
police under U.N. monitoring were investigating the incident.
	   McDowall said there were no more details about the incident, but
other western officials, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said
the attack apparently was a case of personal revenge against one of
the two policemen who recently participated in arresting drug
smugglers.
	   Officials said there were no indications at the moment that the
car bomb was aimed against the joint Muslim-Croat federal police,
which the U.N. is helping to set up despite objections from
hard-liners on both sides.
	   (sl/rp) 	   
</TEXT>
