<HEADLINE>
India, Pakistan to resume talks
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS Pakistani officials not immediately available for comment
in graf 3 &QL; 
 &UR; By HEMA SHUKLA &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   NEW DELHI, India (AP) _ Pakistan has agreed to resume peace
talks on June 22, India announced Friday, an encouraging sign after
nuclear tests by both countries increased tensions in the region.
	   External Affairs spokesman K.C. Singh said Pakistan had
responded in the affirmative to India's proposal to resume talks at
the level of foreign minister, the top bureaucrat in each country's
foreign department, that had stalled last September.
	   Pakistani officials could not immediately be reached for
comment.
