r f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Japan-PunishedBrokera     06-12 0321
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Japan-Punished Brokerages </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Japan to punish brokerages for improper trades
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ Japan's Ministry of Finance said Friday it is
punishing the Tokyo branches of ING Barings Securities Ltd., HSBC
Securities Japan Ltd. and Sumitomo Capital Securities Co. for
improper securities transactions.
	   The Tokyo branch of ING Barings will be banned from proprietary
equity trading June 22 and June 23, and will be banned from
proprietary trading of convertible bonds and equity warrants June
22 to June 28.
	   On May 26 the Securities and Exchange Surveillance Commission
recommended ING Barings be punished for failing to make proper
reports on short selling of securities.
	   The Tokyo branch of HSBC Securities will be banned from
proprietary equity trading and foreign equity trading for customers
on June 22. It will be banned from trading Japanese stocks for
customers from June 22 to July 1.
	   The SESC accused HSBC Securities of submitting false statements,
saying the brokerage told customers that securities trades had been
completed when they weren't, and reported incorrect execution
prices.
	   The Osaka branch of Sumitomo Capital Securities will be banned
from underwriting securities and related activities from June 22 to
June 28 after the commission said the company improperly visited
customers with employees of its parent company, Sumitomo Bank.
	   When Japan allowed banks to set up securities units a few years
ago, it set up ``fire walls'' that prohibited such actions.
	   The ministry also said that the ban on Sumitomo Capital from
underwriting new Japanese government bonds, which was implemented
on May 22, will continue until June 28.
	   In a statement, ING Barings said the SESC inspection resulted
from matters brought to the attention of the Tokyo Stock Exchange
and Finance Ministry by ING Barings itself, and that it fully
cooperated with the authorities.
	   (apdj-jc)	   
</TEXT>
