<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Salas favorite for golden boot after two goal debut
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Chilean striker Marcelo Salas is on a par with
Brazil's Ronaldo in the betting stakes to win the ``golden boot''
award as the top goal-scorer in the World Cup.
	   British bookmakers Ladbrokes on Friday slashed the odds on Salas
from 50-1 to 4-1 _ equal with Ronaldo _ after he scored twice in
Chile's 2-2 draw with Italy on Thursday.
	   Ladbrokes spokesman Sean Boyce said Argentina's Gabriel
Batistuta was next at 6-1, followed by Germany's Oliver Bierhoff at
8-1 and England captain Alan Shearer at 10-1.
	   Boyce said he was expecting plenty of takers for Ladbrokes'
offer of 25-1 on 18-year-old England striker Michael Owen.
	   ``If Owen starts Monday (against Tunisia) you can expect those
odds to come tumbling down,'' he said.
	   ``Already he's hugely popular with football punters (bettors)
because of his increadible strike rate and if it looks like (coach
Glenn) Hoddle will give him the opportunity I expect the floodgates
will open.''
