<HEADLINE>
Margaret Thatcher authorizes biography _ to be published
</HEADLINE>
posthumously &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Former Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher has
authorized a biography on her life and career _ to be published
only after her death.
	   Baroness Thatcher will give special access to her personal and
political papers to the book's author, Charles Moore, editor of the
Daily Telegraph newspaper. But his book cannot appear until she is
dead.
	   The biography on Britain's first female prime minister, who
served in office from 1979 to 1990, is expected to be published in
two or three volumes by Penguin Press.
	   ``This book will be the definitive study of Britain's major
post-war leader, written by one of the most respected
commentators,'' said Andrew Rosenheim, Penguin's managing director.
``It will be among the most important political biographies to
appear in the next century.''
	   Lady Thatcher already has published an autobiography.
	   (kg)
</TEXT>
