<HEADLINE>
`Very good response' to pools, HONGKONG STANDARD
</HEADLINE>
`Very good response' to pools, HONGKONG STANDARD &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   HONGKONG STANDARD
   HONG KONG
   ENGLISH
   Harald BruningASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   CASINO boss Stanley Ho's novel football pools, which kicked off
on Monday in time for the World Cup in France, have stayed mum on
their reported ``very good'' initial response by punters from and
in Hong Kong.
	   A spokesman for SLOT, a subsidiary of Mr Ho's casino monopoly
company STDM running the pools, said yesterday he was unable to
``disclose anything at this point in time'' about the initial
betting turnover, merely saying that it had so far been ``very
good'.' An STDM source said SLOT's silence on its turnover was
``false modesty''.
	   The source said the initial response by punters, including those
from Hong Kong, had been ``very encouraging''.
	   But the source said SLOT was experiencing ``teething problems''
over its vital telebetting operations that were planned to make up
the bulk of the betting turnover.
	   Telebetting accounts can be set up at all branches of the
HongkongBank.
	   A minimum initial deposit of $500 is required.
	   ``It appears they have more applications for telebetting
accounts than they can handle right now,'' the source said.
	   Mr Ho, 76, said last week he expected a betting turnover of up
to a billion patacas (HK$1 billion) during the World Cup in France
alone.
	   Two betting stations started takings bets at noon on Monday.
	   A clerical staff at SLOT, which claims to be Asia's only
government franchised football lottery operator, said yesterday
more than 5,000 telebetting accounts _ most of them from Hong Kong
_ had so far registered.
	   The minimum amount for each telebet is 200 patacas and the
maximum, 200,000 patacas.
	   The lottery's first scheduled betting game was the World Cup
opening match between Brazil and Scotland on Wednesday.
	   
</TEXT>
