<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Paraguay-Bulgaria-Halftime,0305 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Paraguay, Bulgaria play scoreless first half
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MONTPELLIER, France (AP) _ Hristo Stoichkov hit the post late in
the first half but Bulgaria was held to a 0-0 draw at half time in
their World Cup opener against Paraguay on Friday.
	   The Bulgarians, considered favorites in the Group D match,
opened up with several swift atacks and a shot by Kressimir Balakov
that just missed in the second minute.
	   Two minutes later, a Stoichkov was upended in the Paraguayan box
but his pleas to Saudi referee Abdul Rahman Al-Zeid went unheeded.
	   Bulgaria's best chance came in the 35th minute when Stoichkov
took advantage of hesitation by two Paraguayan defenders and hit
the post with a left-footed shot which had Paraguayan keeper Jose
Luis Chilavert totally beaten.
	   The Paraguayans rarely threatened the Bulgarian goal, taking 19
minutes before Carlos Morales' got their first shot, a free kick
that had to be stopped by Bulgarian goalkeeper Zdravko Zdravko with
a diving save.
	   Their best chance came in the 40th minute when forward Jose
Cardoso was left all alone in the Bulgarian penalty area, but his
shot from 15 meters skidded wide of the right post.
	   Stoichkov was yellow-carded in injury time for a reckless
tackle.
	   ___ &QC; 
 &UR; Lineups &QC; 
	   Paraguay_Jose Luis Chilavert, Carlos Gamarra, Celso Ayala, Pedro
Sarabia, Roberto Acuna, Carlos Paredes, Miguel Benitez, Julio Cesar
Enciso, Carlos Morales (Denis Caniza, 45th minute), Jose Cardozo,
Jorge Campos.
	   Bulgaria_Zdravko Zdravkov, Radostin Kischishev, Trifon Ivanov,
Ivaylo Petkov, Zlatko Yankov, Krassimir Balakov, Ilian Iliev,
Anatoli Nankov, Ivaylo Iordanov, Hristo Stoichkov, Luboslav Penev.
	   Referee_Abdul Rahman Al-Zeid, Saudi Arabia.
</TEXT>
