<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Switzerland-Kosovo </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Swiss government halts Kosovo refugee returns
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With Yugoslavia-Kosovo, NATO-Kosovo &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BERN, Switzerland (AP) _ Switzerland is freezing the return of
unsuccessful asylum seekers from the Yugoslav province of Kosovo
until the end of July, Justice Minister Arnold Koller announced
Friday.
	   The reason for the decision was ``the danger of a further
escalation of the conflict in Kosovo,'' Koller told a news
conference.
	   The situation will be reviewed at the end of July, he added.
Those who have committed a criminal offense will not benefit from
the freeze, Koller said.
	   The ruling coalition cabinet has come under intense criticism in
recent weeks for continuing to return rejected asylum seekers to
Kosovo.
	   Last month, the United Nations refugee agency reiterated a plea
made in March to European governments not to send them back.
	   To do so ``would pose security risks for those sent back and
could also tip the scales towards further violence,'' U.N. High
Commissioner for Refugees Sadako Ogata said in a letter.
	   Germany and Switzerland are the two countries with most Kosovo
asylum seekers.
 &UR; (gm)
</TEXT>
