KLibor ends higher in active trade, BUSINESS TIMES
</HEADLINE>
KLibor ends higher in active trade, BUSINESS TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THREE-month KLibor futures on the Malaysia Monetary Exchange
(MME) closed sharply higher yesterday in active trading despite the
cash market closing about unchanged, dealers said.
	   Interest in the futures were quiet as shown by the total of 132
lots being traded yesterday.
	   June 98 was up one tick to 89.00 from 89.01 on Tuesday with 11
lots traded, September 98 rose 12 ticks to 89.06 with 12 lots
traded while December 98 improved 11 ticks to 89.05 with 67 lots
traded.
	   March 99 increased by 15 ticks to 89.05 with 20 lots traded.
	   Total open interest for the day stood at 3,172 contracts versus
3,162 contracts on Tuesday.
	   On the money market, both the underlying Kuala Lumpur Interbank
Offer Rates (KLibor) one-month and three-month money were unchanged
from Tuesday at 11.00 and 11.04 per cent, respectively.
	   
