<HEADLINE>
Dept asked to streamline parks' management, BUSINESS TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Dept asked to streamline parks' management, BUSINESS TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE Department of Wildlife and National Parks has been asked to
look into streamlining the management of state and national parks,
said Minister of Science, Technology and the Enviornment Datuk Law
Hieng Ding.
	   Speaking to reporters after the weekly Cabinet meeting in Kuala
Lumpur yesterday, he said the management of national parks in
Sarawak and Sabah is the responsibility of the State Government.
	   However, the protection of wild animals and wild birds and
national parks falls under the legislative authority of both the
Federal and State Governments.
	   Law said the director-general of the Department of Wildlife and
National Parks, Encik Musa Nordin will meet with state department
directors on this matter.
	   ``There is room to streamline and upgrade the management aspects
of national and state parks, including streamlining legislation and
encouraging more research and development of wildlife species,'' he
said.
	   He added that there is a need to ascertain more effective
conservation efforts as well as look into tightening wildlife
protection laws.
	   Law also called for the setting up of more nature parks for the
conservation and protection of wildlife.
	   ``There is a need to step up public education and awareness
programmes on the importance of endangered species,'' he said.
	   On Monday, Law launched the Asia Conservation Awareness
Programme in Kuala Lumpur which aimed at highlighting the plight of
some endangered animals.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 BUSINESS TIMES all rights reserved as distributed
by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
