<HEADLINE>
Seminar on securities laws, BUSINESS TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Seminar on securities laws, BUSINESS TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE Securities Industry Development Centre of the Securities
Commission (SC) will be holding a public seminar on amendments to
securities laws at Hotel Istana in Kuala Lumpur on June 16 1998.
The one-day seminar will cover topics relating to insider trading,
the importance of corporate disclosure policy, enhancement of
enforcement powers (both civil remedies and criminal enforcement)
and new reporting requirements for companies. SC chairman Datuk Dr
Mohd Munir Abdul Majid will deliver the opening address at the
seminar. Other speakers will be from the SC and the Kuala Lumpur
Stock Exchange. There will also be a panel session which will
include all the speakers, a legal practitioner and a representative
from the Malaysian Association of the Institute of Chartered
Secretaries and Administrators.
	   
