	   KLANG, Thurs. - A 37-year-old man with nine previous convictions
for dadah-related offences and theft was arrested recently in
connection with a snatch theft at Lebuh Turi in Taman Chi Liung.
	   Police also recovered a motorcycle which was reported stolen in
Port Klang on May 30.
	   The man was arrested while attempting to make a getaway after
snatching a gold chain from a 48-year-old information assistant
officer at Lebuh Turi about 5pm on June 4.
	   Klang police chief Assistant Commissioner Karn Kam Peng, said
the officer was walking home when the man rode past her on the
stolen motorcycle and snatched her gold chain.
	   He said the officer put up a fight and the man was making a
getaway with the gold chain when policemen in a patrol car
witnessed the incident and managed to chase and detain the man.
	   ``The officer was not injured in the incident but her blouse was
torn when she put up a fight.''
	   Karn said initial investigations revealed that the suspore than RM5,000 worth of electrical goods, three
hours after they were reported stolen from a house in Taman Sri
Muda yesterday.
	   Police detained a 27-year-old man and recovered the stolen goods
from a house in Taman Alam Megah.
	   
