<HEADLINE>
Homebuyers snap up low-price flats, HONGKONG STANDARD
</HEADLINE>
Homebuyers snap up low-price flats, HONGKONG STANDARD &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   HONGKONG STANDARD
   HONG KONG
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE Paliburg Group received an overwhelming response for its
Park Royale development in Yuen Long indicating that homebuyers are
willing to return to the market for low-price flats.
	   After six days of registration, the group has received more than
900 applications for Park Royale units.
	   This represents an oversubscription of more than 8 times for the
first batch of 100 units at an average price of $2,834 per square
foot.
	   In light of the strong demand, Paliburg has increased the total
available units for sale tomorrow to to 300.
	   It has also increased the average offering price for the last
batch of 50 units to $3,003 per sq ft, representing a 6 per cent
rise compared with the first batch.
	   However, the $3,003 price tag is still cheaper than the
prevailing market price for similar properties in the area since
Paliburg has discounted its price for Parke Royale units by some 15
per cent for the first batch of 100 units.
	   Managing director of Fortune Realty Company, James Tien said the
favourable market response for Park Royale has sent a positive
message to the property market as potential buyers are returning to
the market.
	   He said market demand is still strong if property developers are
willing to launch their projects at low prices.
	   Mr Tien anticipates all 300 units on offer tomorrow will go
quickly.
	   Meanwhile, a Paliburg spokesman said the group planned to
release additional units to the market tomorrow (if all the 300
units are sold quickly), but the number of additional units and the
price has not yet been finalised.
	   The project offers a total of 680 residential units in ten
12-storey towers. Standard sizes range from 650 to 950 sq ft, and
duplex units and penthouses of 1,600 to 2,000 sq ft.
	   
</TEXT>
