	   KLANG, Thurs. - Police have detained a 23-year-old man in
connection with a robbery in Kampung Sungai Udang on May 27 during
which a secondary schoolteacher and her two children were injured.
	   The man was detained in Lorong Masjid off Jalan Yadi on June 3
while he was driving a metallic grey Perodua Kancil bearing the
registration number BEW 5574 belonging to the teacher.
	   Klang police chief Assistant Commissioner Karn Kam Peng said a
police patrol car on crime prevention rounds spotted the car in
Lorong Masjid and ordered the driver to stop.
	   Further investigations showed that the man had pawned a gold
bangle worth RM800 belonging to the teacher at a pawnshop in Klang.
	   The item was later recovered.
	   In the robbery about 9am, a man had come to the teacher's house
on the pretext of looking for the village midwife.
	   When the teacher told him that she did not know who the midwife
was, the man brandished a knife and forced his way into her home.
	   The 30-year-old teacher, who put up a fight, and her
18-month-old son, were slashed.
	   Irritated with the teacher's son and four-year-old daughter
crying, the man grabbed a lesong batu (pestle) and hit the children
and the mother on their heads.
	   The daughter who sustained severe injuries was admitted at the
Tengku Ampuan Rahimah Hospital while the mother and son were
treated as outpatients.
	   
</TEXT>
