	   IPOH, Thurs. - The People's Progressive Party has urged the
Government to grant more permits for the import of rice to ensure
stiffer competition among traders and wholesalers.
	   Its State treasurer Lee Heng said such a move would inevitably
result in lower prices.
	   ``We should not allow one company to monopolise rice imports,''
he said commenting on the recent increase in the price of the super
grade variety.
	   Lee said the Government should continue to open up more land and
utilise idle land for the cultivation of padi as the price increase
had greatly affected the people.
	   ``The Government should also introduce better padi strains to
enable farmers to increase their yields.''
	   
