<SLUG> BC-Spain-Bull Injuries,0210 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Bull run through city leaves 21 injured
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BENAVENTE, Spain (AP) _ A small bull escaped from cordoned off
streets during a bull run and rampaged through the streets of the
northwestern Spanish town of Benavente, injuring 21 people.
	   A 13-year-old girl was gored in her genitals and another two
women in the legs Thursday, said the Hospital Comarcal de Benavente
in a statement Friday. Their conditions were not serious.
	   The rest of the wounded were lightly injured in falls or by
rushing crowds when they tried to avoid being tossed or gored after
the bull broke a security fence and ran through the city.
	   The bull was shot and killed half an hour later by the Civil
Guard who cornered it in a downtown street.
	   In Benavente, like many other northern and central Spanish
towns, bulls are run through cordoned-off streets to the town's
bull ring. Professional matadors fight them later in the day.
	   The San Fermin festival in Pamplona is the country's most
well-known and has been held almost continuously since 1591. It
became internationally famous with Ernest Hemingway's 1926 novel,
``The Sun Also Rises'' and attracts hundreds of thousands of people
each year.
	   Dozens are hurt in the runs each year. 	   
</TEXT>
