<HEADLINE>
EU urges Nigeria return to democracy
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The European Union on Friday urged the new
government in Nigeria to move quickly to elect a civilian
government.
	   ``The EU welcomes Gen. (Abdulsalam) Abubakar's call to all
Nigerians to join in a process of reconstruction and
reconciliation,'' said the statement issued by Britain's Foreign
Office on behalf of the 15-nation European Union.
	   ``This, together with the release of detainees and the
restoration of the rule of law would be important steps in a
process leading to Nigeria's return to its rightful place in the
international community.''
