<HEADLINE>
DSE marks moderate rise, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
DSE marks moderate rise, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The All Share Price Index of the Dhaka Stock Exchange (DSE)
marked a moderate rise by 7.27 points yesterday.The day witnessed
decline in the gainers number further with an increased turnover.
The All Share Price Index of the day stood at 692.66 points against
previous day's 685.39. The performance of some blue chip was good
that helped increase the price index and the market capitalisation.
Of them, the share of BATBC Ltd, held the first highest position in
the market capitalisation, and Beximco Pharmaceuticals Ltd,
captured the second highest position, advanced prominently.
	   The former gained by Taka 5.44 to Taka 116.69 and the latter
gained by Taka 2.61 to Taka 70.51 against their face value of Taka
10. Other companies having high market capital gained on the day
were: IDLC by Taka 26.77, United Leasing Company Ltd by Taka 10.00,
Square Pharmaceuticals Ltd by Taka 25.51, Monno Fabrics Ltd by Taka
2.61, BOC Bangladesh Ltd by Taka 0.61 and Shinepukur Holdings Ltd
by Taka 0.91.On the other hand, Singer Bangladesh Ltd of the group
incurred a loss of Taka 22.57 per share while Chittagong Cement
Clinker had a loss of Taka 5.26 per share.
	   Other prominent losers for trading the single share were:
National Tubes ltd by Taka 24.00, Islamai Bank Bangladesh Ltd by
Taka 110.46 and IBN Sinha Pharmaceuticals Ltd by Taka 18.00 while
Beximco Pharmaceuticals Ltd emerged as the value leader for having
a transaction of Taka 5.26 million in yesterday's trading.
	   
</TEXT>
