	   The Union Bangladesh Index yesterday ended 1.34% (3.48 points)
higher to close at 290.90. Daily turnover also increased by 22%.
Overall market sentiment was positive as demand was well supported
by supply. Of the traded blue-chip stocks gainers outnumbered
losers by 16 to 13.
	   Although Prime Textile (5.59%) was the top gainer of the day,
only 740 shares were traded. Beximco Pharmaceuticals added 3.84% on
retail demand. Reckitt and Colman, the top loser of the day,
declined 3.05% with a very thin volume (100) followed by Apex
Tannery, which declined 1.95% on retail selling.
	   
