	   PASIR MAS, Thurs. - Two children drowned while playing in a padi
field near Kampung Pangkal Danan, Kedondong, yesterday.
	   They were identified as Mohd Farizal Zulkifli, 7, and his
four-year-old cousin Mohd Rosdan Rosli.
	   District police chief Acting Superintendent Jalil Talib said the
children went with their grandfather Mustafa Yusuf, 57, about
9.30am.
	   ``Mohd Farizal and Mohd Rosdan followed Mustafa to the padi
field to catch fish,'' he said, adding that the children were left
alone when Mustafa returned to his house, 200 metres away, about
half an hour later.
	   Jalil said Mustafa found the boys missing when he returned to
the padi field about 30 minutes later.
	   He said villagers, who helped in the search for the boys, found
their bodies near the area where they were reported missing.
	   ``Their bodies were found about 11am in a drain which had three
metres of water near the padi field,'' he said.
	   In Kuantan, the body of a 15-year-old boy who drowned while
fishing at Sungai Semantan, Mentakab, yesterday was found this
morning.
	   Pahang Criminal Investigation Department chief Assistant
Commissioner Sulaiman Mahmud said the body of Ang Chi Seng of Taman
Bukit Bendera in Mentakab was recovered by police at about 11am.
	   The victim's mother Lan Kam Hong, 36, lodged a report at the
Mentakab police station.
	   She told police that Ang, a Form Three pupil had skipped school
to go fishing at the river yesterday.
	   
</TEXT>
