<HEADLINE>
Officials shorten course in attempt to play European Grand Prix
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: WILL lead with conclusion of play &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   SLALEY, England (AP) _ Officials of the rain-delayed European
Grand Prix went to unusual lengths Friday to start play.
	   All first-round play Thursday was washed out.
	   On Friday, after waiting until mid-afternoon for the rain to
stop, play began with the Slaley Hall course reconfigured to a
par-69 instead of the usual par-72.
	   Officials reduced the pars on the 12th, 13th and 18th holes. The
tees on those three were brought forward to assure tee shots would
clear bog-like areas on the fairways.
	   Rain and daylight permitting, officials said they planned to
play 18 holes on Friday and Saturday with a 36-hole final on Sunday
in the 650,000-pound (dlrs 1.06 million) European event.
	   (scw)	   
