	   KOTA KINABALU, Thurs. - A new headquarters for the Sabah Road
Transport Department costing RM16.8 million is being built on a
5.6ha site in Jalan Bundusan near here.
	   Deputy Transport Minister Datuk Wira Ali Rustam said the
construction of the new headquarters is part of the RTD's ongoing
efforts to improve its services and ease congestion.
	   Speaking to reporters after inspecting the project site, Ali
said it was 20 per cent completed and would be ready as scheduled
in September next year.
	   It will, among others, have three drive-in counters for the
convenience of the public.
	   Ali said new RTD offices will be built for the Sandakan and
Tawau divisions.
	   ``We have already identified the sites but the projects can only
take off after the economic situation improves,'' he said, adding
that the RTD has already built new offices in seven districts and
eight sub-districts in the State.
	   Ali also announced that effective this month lorry owners in
Sabah could pay road tax on a monthly basis.
	   
