<SLUG> BC-Yugoslavia-Kosovo, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Albanian militants kill Serb policemen near Kosovo capital
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with fighting resuming in Decani region. &QL; 
 &UR; BY ISMET HAJDARI &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia (AP) _ Ethnic Albanian militants, boldly
stepping up their attacks, killed two Serb policemen just a few
miles from Kosovo's capital and on Friday promised to come out of
their shadowy underground and show they are a mass organization.
	   Fighting between Serbian forces and the militants also erupted
again in the Decani region in western Kosovo, close to the border
with Albania. It was a Serbian offensive there last week that
prompted NATO Thursday to announce a show of air power to try and
persuade Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic to halt such
assault.
	   Ethnic Albanian sources claimed that six villages in the Decani
area were under attack, including from grenade launchers normally
issued not to Serbian police, but to the Yugoslav army.
	   There was no independent confirmation of their report, but the
state-run Tanjug news agency in Belgrade reported that a Serb
policeman was seriously hurt in what it called an attack by ``armed
Albanian terrorists'' near one of the villages, Prilep.
 &UR; Serb sources, 2nd graf, BC-Yugoslavia-Kosovo
	   (ih/kk/as)
