<SLUG> BC-Sports-Baseball-Japan Roundup </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Swallows beat Giants 6-3
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ The Central League's last-place Yakult Swallows
batted in five runs in the top of the first inning Friday as they
edged the front-running Yomiuri Giants 6-3 at Tokyo Dome.
	   In the third inning, Dwayne Hosey, formerly with the Boston Red
Sox, hit a solo homer, his sixth this season.
	   Yakult starter Kazuhisa Ishii collected his sixth win as he gave
up five hits and walked two, while striking out 10 in eight
innings.
	   At Koshien, Tomonori Maeda hit a winning double in the top of
the 12th inning, driving in two runs that ended a seesaw game,
lifting the Hiroshima Toyo Carp to a 6-5 victory over the Hanshin
Tigers.
	   Carp's left-hander Ken Takahashi gave up only four hits, walked
two and struck out four in eight innings.
	   The Carp ended a losing streak at four and rose to second place,
dropping the Chunichi Dragons to third.
	   At Nagoya, in central Japan, Hitoshi Nakane hit a solo homer in
the top of the fifth inning, his first this season, as the Yokohama
BayStars blanked the Dragons 2-0.
	   Norihiro Komada drove in another run on his sacrifice fly in the
seventh.
	   In Pacific League action, Koichiro Yoshinaga drove in a winning
run on a double in the bottom of the 10th inning, giving the
Fukuoka Daiei Hawks a 5-4 victory over the Nippon Ham Fighters at
home.
	   Now the Fighters are only a half game behind the first-place
Fighters.
	   At Chiba, pinch hitter Koichi Hori batted in a tie-breaking run
on a single in the bottom of the seventh inning, as the Chiba Lotte
Marines edged the Orix BlueWave 2-1 at home.
	   Harvey Pulliam, formerly of the Colorado Rockies, hit a solo
homer for the BlueWave in the seventh but it came too late.
	   The Seibu Lions and the Kintetsu Buffaloes were idle Friday.
 &UR; (may)
