<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-US-Nuclear </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ukraine to get additional dlrs 78 million in American aid
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ The United States will give Ukraine another
dlrs 78 million to dismantle the rest of its nuclear weapons
facilities and convert defense industries to civilian uses.
	   An agreement was signed in Kiev on Friday by U.S. Defense
Department coordinator Laura Holgate and three Ukrainian military
and government officials.
	   Ukraine inherited the world's third-largest nuclear arsenal with
the 1991 collapse of the Soviet Union. It has surrendered all its
nuclear warheads to Russia and pledged to remain nuclear-free, but
still needs to destroy some of the nuclear infrastructure.
	   Under the agreement, dlrs 76.7 million was earmarked for the
elimination of silo launchers, training silos, launch control
centers and liquid rocket fuel.
	   It will also be used to eliminate about 40 strategic bombers and
more than 1,000 air-launched cruise missiles, the U.S. Embassy in
Kiev said.
	   Another dlrs 730,000 is for the conversion of Ukraine's defense
industry to civilian uses, and dlrs 630,000 is for the
establishment of an effective export-control regime to prevent the
proliferation of weapons of mass destruction.
	   The two sides also agreed Friday to extend until 2001 the
deadline for Ukraine to destroy its nuclear weapons infrastructure.
	   ``These and similar projects will allow Ukraine to pursue its
goal of eliminating all nuclear weapons' delivery systems and their
accompanying infrastructure,'' the embassy said in a statement.
	   The new money brings to dlrs 520 million the amount of aid
provided by the U.S. Department of Defense for threat reduction
programs in Ukraine.
	   (sms/ls) 	   
</TEXT>
