Flood situation in Sylhet static, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Flood situation in Sylhet static, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The overall flood situation in the district remained static with
reports of eight deaths in flood related causes.
	   Nearly one lakh acres of aus and aman paddy of 11 thanas went
under water and thousands of people have been marooned by the flood
water.
	   The worst affected thanas are Companiganj, Zakiganj, Biyanibazar
and Goainghat.
	   There has been a outbreak of water borne diseases in the flood
affected areas due to lack of drinking water and relief materials.
	   Of the deaths two people- Abdur Rashid Haripur and Salim of
Panichhara villages in Jaintapur thana-were killed by land-slide.
	   Five deaths were reported from Jainta thana.
	   
