	   Different socio-political and trade bodies on Thursday hailed
the proposed budget for the year 1998-99 saying that it was fully
people-oriented and would help fulfil the hopes and aspirations of
the nation.
	   Giving an immediate reaction on the budget, they said through
the budget the real pro-people outlook of the present government
has been reflected.
	   The leaders of these organisations congratulated the present
government for giving the highest allocation to the education
sector in the budget. ``This allocation will help eradicate the
curse of illiteracy and produce skilled manpower,'' they said.
	   They, however, said that the new budget would play a vital role
in expanding trade and commerce and rehabilitating sick industries
in the country.
	   General Secretary of Awami League and LGRD and Coopertives
Minister Zillur Rahman hailed the proposed budget, describing it as
timely, epoch-making, people-oriented and milestone for balanced
development.
	   In an instant reaction, Rahman said the proposed budget
manifested the Awami League government's willingness to fulfil its
pre-election pledges and help face the challenges of the twenty
first century.
	   Prominent, among those, who hailed the budget are: AKM
Shamsuddoha, member of Executive Committee of the FBCCI and
Councillor, Dhaka Stock Exchange, National Association of Small and
Cottage Industries of Bangladesh (NASCIB), National Tax Lawyers'
Association (NTLA), Pabna Chamber of Commerce and Industry,
Bangladesh Truck Owners' Association, Bangladesh Gold Industry
Workers' League, Pachatturer Ghatak Nirmul Committee and former
State Minister for LGRD and Cooperatives Abul Hossain, MP.
	   
