<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Key defender Vidovic out of opening clash against the
</HEADLINE>
Dutch &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MONTHIEUX, France (AP) _ Belgian defender Gordan Vidovic is
unable to start Saturday's World Cup Group E opener against the
Netherlands because of a strained abductor muscle, coach Georges
Leekens said.
	   Vidovic had been key in Belgium's promising preparation
campaign, but Leekens insisted on resting him for the vital second
game against Mexico next week.
	   ``I don't want to take any risks. It's the game against Mexico
that will be decisive in the first round, not the one against the
Dutch,'' he said.
	   Leekens has long maintained that the Red Devils are too inferior
to the Dutch to mount a credible challenge, focusing his efforts on
the Mexico game and the first-round closer against South Korea
instead.
	   He still has to decide whether to replace Vidovic with Lierse's
Eric Van Meir or Anderlecht's Glen De Boeck.
	   For Saturday's game at Saint-Denis' Stade de France, Leekens
will sideline veteran Enzo Scifo, preferring to stick with the
brawn of Schalke 04 midfielder Marc Wilmots.
	   The attack will be spearheaded by Fiorentina's Luis Oliveira and
PSV Eindhoven's Luc Nilis.
	   Belgium also was the underdog when the neighbors and age-old
rivals played at the 1994 World Cup and Belgium surprisingly
prevailed 1-0. But during the World Cup qualifiers, the Dutch beat
the Belgians 3-0 and 3-1.
	   (rac-sl)
</TEXT>
