<HEADLINE>
Ministry: 46,643 laid off since July, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Ministry: 46,643 laid off since July, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Thurs. - A total of 46,643 workers were retrenched
from July last year until June 6, with the manufacturing sector
accounting for 60.5 per cent of them.
	   In figures released today, the Human Resources Ministry said
86.7 per cent of the workers were Malaysians.
	   The Ministry said women accounted for 38.4 per cent or 12,853 of
the 33,510 workers retrenched up till last month.
	   Selangor with 8,314 had the highest number of retrenched
workers, followed by Kuala Lumpur (5,177), Penang (4,955),
Kedah/Perlis (3,382) and Sarawak (2,751).
	   The Ministry said the number of people registering with the
Labour Department was increasing while vacancies were fluctuating.
	   It said monthly placements averaged about 1,900 workers.
	   The Ministry said that from Feb 17 until June 4, the Technical
Committee in the Home Ministry had vetted 325 applications
involving 77,431 foreign workers for the manufacturing and
plantation sectors.
	   
