<SLUG> BC-Czech-Nuclear </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Cooling substance leaks from Dukovany nuclear plant
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PRAGUE, Czech Republic (AP) _ Two to three cubic meters of a
cooling substance leaked from the primary circuit in the Dukovany
nuclear plant Friday morning, the news agency CTK reported.
	   Nobody was injured in the accident that occurred at 0935 (0735
GMT), the agency said.
	   It quoted Jan Suller of the National Institute for Nuclear
Security as saying that no leaks of radioactivity were recorded
outside the plant.
	   The 1,760-megawatt, Soviet-designed Dukovany plant, about 200
kilometers (120 miles) southeast of Prague, is the only nuclear
plant operating in the Czech Republic at present.
	   Another 2,000-megawatt plant is being built in Temelin, about 50
kilometers (30 miles) from the Austrian border. The plant is
expected to go on line in the year 2000.
	   (nr/rp) 	   
