<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Japan-Cult Attack </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Japanese cult member said guru ordered attack
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ A former senior member of the cult accused in the
1995 nerve gas attack on the Tokyo subways testified Friday that
the group's guru ordered an assault on a lawyer critical of the
cult, a news report said.
	   Seiichi Endo, 37, the cult's biological scientist, told the
Tokyo District Court that Shoko Asahara ordered cult members to
spray the deadly sarin nerve gas on lawyer Taro Takimoto's car in
1994, Kyodo News agency reported.
	   Endo was testifying in the trial of former cult lawyer Yoshinobu
Aoyama, 38, charged with attempted murder in the attack on
Takimoto, who survived. Endo is also charged with attempted murder
in the same case.
	   Endo said Asahara, who is on trial for murder in the subway
gassing, ordered members to practice spraying the gas, and gave
directions on how the attack should be carried out, the report
said.
	   Takimoto was helping families of cult members at the time of the
attack in May 1994.
	   Endo is charged in nine criminal cases, including the subway
attack, which killed 12 and injured thousands.
	   (jc)
</TEXT>
