<HEADLINE>
Puncak Niaga says sorry for inconvenience, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Puncak Niaga says sorry for inconvenience, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   PETALING JAYA, Thurs. - Motorists using Jalan Universiti which
has been turned into a one-way street due to pipe-laying works,
have been urged to be patient and bear with the inconvenience.
	   ``I apologise for the inconvenience but I hope everyone
understands that this project is very necessary to help solve the
current water woes,''
	   Puncak Niaga (M) Sdn Bhd executive chairman Datuk Rozali Ismail
told reporters after visiting the worksite in front of the
International Islamic University today.
	   He said Puncak Niaga would try to complete the works, scheduled
to take four months, as soon as possible. ``In the meantime, we are
continuously meeting with the Petaling Jaya Municipal Council to
see what we can do to ease the traffic congestion,''
	   he said, adding that more signs would be placed at various
places to inform and warn the public of road diversions.
	   The 1,800mm-diametre pipe being laid is part of a 71km supply
pipeline which will bring water from the Sungai Selangor Water
Supply Scheme Phase Two in Bukit Badong, Kuala Selangor, to the
Bukit Gasing reservoir.
	   The reservoir is expected to end the current rationing exercise
for consumers in Sections 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 11, 12, 14, 16, 17 and
Taman Seaport when the pipeline, which has a capacity of 250
million litres per day, is completed by the end of the year.
	   
</TEXT>
