	   MUAR, Thurs. - A shellfish collector had the shock of her life
when she found carcasses of monkeys on the branches of mangrove
trees and in the swamps near Parit Jawa fishing village today.
	   Rahmah Ibrahim, 40, said: ``From the stench, I believe the
monkeys must have died a few days ago.''
	   She believed the animals must have died after eating poisoned
fruits as there were some near the carcasses.
	   Village businessman Mansur Poh said he had reported the matter
to the Wildlife and National Parks Department.
	   
