	   IT started out as Fire, then it was Energy. Now, it's Lost City.
In case you're wondering how this new-look joint in Kuala Lumpur
rates, Lost City is a great pick for night-crawlers.
	   Just two weeks old, it has everything - from a disco to karaoke
and music spinned by deejays to live shows.
	   Currently cooking up a storm are two experienced bands (not from
the Philippines, mind you!) called Freedom and N.R.G.
	   Yes, you've seen and heard them before. Freedom (of Mulanya Di
Sini fame) alternates with N.R.G. (which certainly has a helluva
lot of energy!!!) nightly with their brand of rock, pop, Top 40
hits and the works.
	   Freedom, with Shuib on drums, belts out hits such as Elton
John's The Way You Look Tonight, Joan Jett's I Hate Myself For
Loving You and Celine Dion's My Heart Will Go On.
	   And you simply have to watch N.R.G. This nine-member band has
great showmanship and delivers solid renditions of current
chart-toppers. Almost all its members can sing, but the best part
is that you can, too. How?
	   Simply ``get lost'' in any of the 16 karaoke rooms which are
free if you book for a certain period. In other words, have a solid
three-hour concert there yourself!!! Also, check out Ning Baizura
who will be appearing tonight and tomorrow, at 10pm.
	   Lost City is open daily until 1am. It is located in Lorong P.
Ramlee.
	   You can't miss it.
	   
