<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,0961 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Overnight, skies were variably cloudy across the east third of
Puerto Rico eastward through the U.S. Virgin Islands. Doppler radar
noted widely scattered to scattered showers, a few locally heavy
moving westward less than 10 mph and across this area. Showers will
continue here until around 8 a.m. Mostly clear to partly cloudy
skies persisted elsewhere across Puerto Rico. Predawn coastal
temperatures ranged from around 70 degrees across west Puerto Rico
to the upper 70s elsewhere across Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin
Islands.
	   The upper-level trough which contributed to recent heavy rains
continued to weaken and for this afternoon this should prevent the
development of heavy showers across most of the local area. Still,
the local atmosphere remained unstable enough for daytime heating
interacting with the sea breeze and mountain influences to spark
scattered showers and isolated afternoon thunderstorms across
mainly the western highlands and west sections of Puerto Rico.
	   The next tropical wave expected to affect our region was located
overnight over the central tropical Atlantic and is expected to
move into the eastern Caribbean during the first part of the coming
week.
 &UR; San Juan and north sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Partly cloudy and breezy. A 30 percent chance of
showers
	   Morning east and afternoon west. High 85 to 90. Wind east 10 to
15 mph except northeast along the coast.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy east with a 30 percent chance of
showers. Fair west. Low 70 to 80. Wind east less than 10 mph.
	   Saturday ... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Isolated thunderstorms. High around 90.
 &UR; East sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Variably cloudy morning. Becoming mostly sunny
afternoon. A 30 percent chance of morning showers. High from 75
mountains to 85 to 90 coasts. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight ... Variably cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low from 65 to 70 mountains to 75 to 80 coasts. Wind east less than
10 mph.
	   Saturday ... Partly cloudy morning with a 30 percent chance of
showers. Mostly sunny afternoon. High from 75 mountains to 85 to 90
coasts. Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 mph.
 &UR; Ponce and south sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers,
mainly east in morning and west in afternoon. Isolated afternoon
thunderstorms inland. High 80 to 90. Wind east 10 to 15 mph except
southeast along the coast.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy east with a 20 percent chance of
showers. Fair west. Low from around 65 interior to 75 to 80 coasts.
Wind light northeast.
	   Saturday ... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers,
mainly east in the morning and west in the afternoon. Isolated
thunderstorms. High 80 to around 90. Wind southeast 10 to 15 mph.
 &UR; Mayaguez and west sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Mostly sunny morning. Becoming variably cloudy
afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms.
High 85 to 90. Wind east 10 to 15 mph except for an afternoon sea
breeze less than 10 mph along the coast.
	   Tonight ... Becoming generally fair. Low 65 to 75. Wind light
east.
	   Saturday ... Mostly sunny morning. Becoming variably cloudy
afternoon with a 30 percent chance of showers. Isolated
thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east 10 to 15 mph except for an
afternoon sea breeze less than 10 mph along the coast.
 &UR; Interior sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Partly cloudy morning. Becoming mostly cloudy
afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers. Isolated
thunderstorms. High from around 75 mountains to 85 to 90 lower
elevations. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight ... Becoming partly cloudy east with a 20 percent chance
of showers. Fair west. Low 65 to 75. Wind east less than 10 mph.
	   Saturday ... Partly cloudy morning. Becoming variably cloudy
afternoon with a 30 percent chance of showers. Isolated
thunderstorms. High from around 75 mountains to 85 to 90 lower
elevations. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
 &UR; St. Thomas, St. John and St. Croix
	   Today ... Partly cloudy morning. Mostly sunny afternoon. A 30
percent chance of morning showers. High 80 to 90. Wind east 15 mph.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
Low 70 to 80. Wind east less than 10 mph.
	   Saturday ... Variably cloudy with a 30 percent chance of
showers. Isolated thunderstorms. High 80 to 90. Wind to southeast
10 to 15 mph.
 &UR; Puerto Rico and U.S. Virgin Islands waters
	   Synopsis ... Surface high pressure extending from the east
central Atlantic west-southwest to the Bahamas will continue to
produce a moderate to fresh east to southeast wind flow across the
local waters through Saturday. A weakening tropical wave located
just west of the local waters late this morning will continue
moving west through Saturday.
 &UR; Atlantic waters
	   This afternoon ... Wind east to southeast 10 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to
5 ft. Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight ... Wind east to southeast around 10 kt. Seas 2 to 4 ft.
Scattered showers.
	   Saturday ... Wind southeast to east 10 to 15 kt. Seas 3 to 4 ft.
Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
 &UR; Caribbean waters
