	   CRUDE palm oil futures on the Kuala Lumpur Commodity Exchange
extended Wednesday's gains on the back of a weak ringgit but many
players stayed sidelined.
	   At the close, June gained RM23 to settle at RM2,368, July rose
RM23.00 to RM2,348, August added RM20.00 to RM2,325 and September
gained RM20.00 to RM2,310.
	   Turnover declined to 863 lots from 1,489 lots on Wednesday and
open interest decreased to 6,484 contracts from 6,509 contracts.
	   JF Apex Futures Sdn Bhd said players stayed on the sidelines as
they awaited for fresh leads.
	   The futures prices opened slightly higher in the morning on a
weak ringgit but weakened in the afternoon when the ringgit
rebounded.
	   
