<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Bomb Threat, 1st Ld-Writethru,0206 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Bomb threat forces evacuation of stadium press box
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with journalists evacuated from press center after
game. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MONTPELLIER, France (AP) _ Bomb threats emptied the press box at
Montpellier stadium before Friday's match between Bulgaria and
Paraguay. A media center next to the stadium also was briefly
evacuated about an hour after the game.
	   Eric Champel, a member of the organizing committee, said two
threatening phone calls were received about 2 1/2 hours before the
match was scheduled to start.
	   ``We briefly evacuated the press stands and brought in the
sniffing dogs, but that's our usual procedure before every game at
the World Cup,'' he said, adding that there was no concern for the
security at the match.
	   Most of the evacuated reporters found out about the threats only
after the all-clear had been given.
	   About one hour after the game, all journalists were instructed
to leave the nearby media center. Security officers, speaking on
condition of anomimity, said there was another bomb threat.
	   Journalists were allowed back into the building some 15 minutes
later.
	   (ds-sl)
</TEXT>
