<HEADLINE>
Crippled during Abacha years, Nigerian opposition keeps fighting
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: LEADS with two grafs to UPDATE with aides to main opposition
leader saying he was arrested. Pickup 2nd graf pvs: In the Yaba
... &QL; 
 &UR; By TIM SULLIVAN &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) _ Firing canisters of tear gas into the air,
riot police dispersed groups of protesters in Nigeria's commercial
capital Friday before the activists could converge for a mass
demonstration.
	   Aides to Gani Fawehinmi, a lawyer and leading dissident who
organized the protests, told The Associated Press he was arrested.
If confirmed, it would be a serious blow to an opposition already
weakened by the imprisonment or exile of most of its main leaders.
