</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Jordan-Shooting, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Family of 11 shot to death in a mysterious crime
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: UPDATES with arrest of son who confessed to murder
 &UR; AP Photo AMM101

<TEXT>
	   AMMAN, Jordan (AP) _ Police arrested Friday the son of a family
that was wiped out in a 12-person murder which has shocked Jordan.
	   One or more gunmen shot school bus driver Amin Qashash, 50, his
wife, four children, a son-in-law and four grandchildren before
dawn Thursday in their home in Banayat, a village 20 kilometers (12
miles) northwest of Amman, government officials said.
	   Police announced they had arrested Qashash's son, Saeed, 18, but
did not say if he had any accomplices.
	   Saeed had confessed to killing his family out of fear that he
might fail his high school exams, police said.
	   The family was shot in their house's basement and a brick wall
was then built to hide its entrance, an official said, speaking on
condition of anonymity.
	   Jordan, which is proud of its reputation for security in a
volatile region, has been shaken recently by a series of shootings
and bombings.
