<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Kyrgyzstan-Explosion </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Third explosion in two weeks in Kyrgyz city of Osh
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ An explosion in an apartment building injured six
people Friday in the city of Osh in western Kyrgyzstan, a news
agency reported. It was the third explosion in two weeks, ITAR-Tass
said.
	   All three explosions were blamed on gas, the Interior Ministry
press service told ITAR-Tass. The owner hooked his apartment
building to the city gas system without taking proper precautions,
it said.
	   But the Security Ministry said the first two blasts in the
Central Asian country _ on a bus and in a house of May 30 and 31 _
involved homemade bombs.
	   It said that four people have been arrested, all members of a
fundamentalist sect of Islam, Wahhabism, that has been blamed for
recent violence in several parts of the former Soviet Union.
	   ITAR-Tass said that police patrols have been increased in Osh
and checkpoints set up on the town outskirts to inspect vehicles
from other regions.
	   Osh is located near the border with Uzbekistan. Clashes between
ethnic Kyrgyz and Uzbeks were common even during Soviet times.
	   (ls) 	   
</TEXT>
