<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Denmark-Saudi Arabia-Halftime,0287 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Danes, Saudis 0-0 at halftime
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LENS, France (AP) _ Ebbe Sand and Martin Jorgensen squandered
two easy chances as Denmark dominated but was held 0-0 by Saudi
Arabia in the first half of their World Cup Group C game Friday.
	   The Danes had a great chance to take an 18th minute lead when
Morten Wieghorst climbed above the Saudi defense to meet a free
kick and head the ball into the danger area. But Sand, with only
the 'keeper to beat, prodded the ball over the bar from eight
meters (yards).
	   Jorgensen wasted another good opening in the 32nd when Brian
Laudrup sliced open the Saudi defense with an angled, forward pass.
But the Udinese striker, well clear of the defense, fired well wide
from close range.
	   The Saudi defense failed to clear a free kick a minute later and
Marc Rieper almost scrambled the ball in from four meters out.
	   The Saudi strikeforce made little impression in the opening 40
minutes of the game but Danish 'keeper Peter Schmeichel made a
diving, fingertip save from a free kick by Saeed Owairan just
before the break, although the ball appeared to be going inches
wide of the post.
	   Lineups:
	   Denmark _ Peter Schmeichel, Michael Schjonberg, Marc Rieper, Jes
Hogh, Thomas Helveg, Michael Laudrup, Brian Laudrup, Soren Colding,
Morten Wieghorst, Ebbe Sand, Martin Jorgensen.
	   Saudi Arabia _ Mohammed Al Deayea, Mohammed Al Jahani, Mohammed
Al Khilaiwi, Abdullah Zubromawi, Fuad Amin, Ibrahim Al Shahrani,
Sami Al Jaber, Saeed Owairan, Hussain Sulimani, Khalid Al Muwalid,
Youssef Al Thyniyan.
	   Referee _ Javier Alberto Castrilli, Argentina.
	   (mc/mm-rjm)	   
</TEXT>
