	   THE Selangor Government has approved the Petaling Jaya Municipal
Council's application to extend the operating hours of nightspots
in Petaling Jaya to 1am on weekdays and 2am on weekends and public
holidays. They now have to close midnight.
	   A council (MPPJ) official said this would be in tandem with
Kuala Lumpur City Hall's move to extend operating hours of
nightspots.
	   The official said the decision would be enforced immediately.
	   The council had earlier this year submitted the application.
	   There are 90 licenced entertainment outlets in the municipality.
	   The council is in the process of renewing the entertainment
licences for the operators which is issued on a yearly basis.
	   
