<HEADLINE>
Graf to meet DFS Classic title-holder in semifinals
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS Graf quotes in grafs 4-7

<TEXT>
	   BIRMINGHAM, England (AP) _ Steffi Graf, improving with each
match in her preparation for Wimbledon, advanced to the semifinals
of the DFS Classic with a straight-set victory Friday over Spain's
Maria Luisa Serna.
	   The seven-time Wimbledon champion took 68 minutes to beat Serna
6-4, 6-4 and set up a semifinal clash with defending title holder
Nathalie Tauziat of France.
	   Graf, playing only her third tournament since a knee operation
last June, dropped only one service game to the left-hander from
Barcelona.
	   The German said her comeback was progressing better than she had
expected.
	   ``I hoped I would have two matches here and now I'm going to
have four, which I'm delighted to have,'' she said.
	   Graf, who has a 19-0 record against Tauziat, said she was
physically fit and keen as ever to win.
	   ``It isn't difficult for me to motivate myself,'' she said. ``I
enjoy playing and the game still fascinates me enough to go out
there.''
	   Earlier, the third-seeded Tauziat downed unseeded Australian
Kerry-Anne Guse 6-2, 6-3.
	   Tauziat had two priorities Friday _ advance to the semifinals
and then get away in time to watch France play South Africa in the
World Cup.
	   ``I love football but I'm happy not to be in Paris during the
World Cup because there are so many people there now,'' she said.
``I will be quite happy watching it on television.''
	   The other DFS Classic semifinal will be between Elena
Likhovtseva, the seventh seed from Russia, and Indonesia's Yayuk
Basuki, the No. 6 seed and 1997 runner-up.
	   Likhovtseva beat Belgium's Monique Van Roost 6-3, 6-4, while
Basuki beat No. 2 seed Irina Spirlea 6-4, 5-7, 7-5.
</TEXT>
