<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Paraguay-Bulgaria, 4th Ld-Writethru,0554 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Paraguayan goalkeeper almost makes history
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: Optional lead; UPDATES with more Chilavert comments, Bonev
quotes; edits to tighten. &QL; 
 &UR; By DUSAN STOJANOVIC &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   MONTPELLIER, France (AP) _ Jose Luis Chilavert almost made World
Cup history. And he is irked that he missed his chance.
	   Bulgarian Goalkeeper Zdravko Zdravkov fully stretched to his
upper right to deny his flamboyant Paraguayan counterpart on a
second-half, 25-meter free kick, leaving Bulgaria and Paraguay with
a goalless draw in their World Cup opener Friday.
	   ``I already saw the ball in the net,'' said Chilavert, who has
35 goals in his professional career. ``Too bad, I could have made
history.''
	   No goalkeeper has ever scored in a World Cup match except in a
penalty shootout.
	   The 32-year-old Chilavert has a reputation for his offensive
forays, in addition to a temper.
	   Chilavert's 78th-minute chance was the highlight of a match that
saw few good opportunities _ and poor finishing by both sides on
the ones that were created.
	   Bulgaria had its chance in the 35th minute when Hristo Stoichkov
beat two defenders and knocked the ball off the right post with a
left-footed shot which had Chilavert totally beaten.
	   The Bulgarians played the final two minutes with only 10 men
after Anatoli Nankov earned his second yellow. Paraguay had two
chances following the sending off, but failed to convert.
	   Paraguay dominated the second half, getting several chances
before Chilavert's free kick.
	   ``We lacked poise to finish the plays,'' Paraguay coach Paulo
Cesar Carpeggiani said. ``We always missed the last pass.''
	   Stoichkov set up the best Bulgarian opportunity in the second
half when he charged into the box from the left, crossed the ball
to an unmarked Luboslav Penev, who blasted high from six yards with
only Chilavert to beat.
	   ``We had some tactical errors on both sides of the defense,''
Carpeggiani said. ``But we made some adjustments and improved in
the second half. Unfortunately, it wasn't enough to win. We lacked
the finishing touch.''
	   The match was a game of missed opportunities.
	   In the fifth minute, Stoichkov was upended in the Paraguayan box
but his pleas to Saudi referee Abdul Rahman Al-Zeid went unheeded.
	   ``It was a 100 percent penalty,'' Bulgarian coach Hristo Bonev
said. ``We played well in the first half, but our game collapsed in
the second.''
	   Stoichkov was yellow-carded in injury time for a reckless
tackle.
	   ``Paraguay was supposed to be an easy team to beat, but this is
not so and I feel very proud of what we've done,'' Chilavert said.
	   ___ &QC; 
 &UR; Lineups &QC; 
	   Paraguay_Jose Luis Chilavert; Carlos Gamarra, Celso Ayala, Pedro
Sarabia, Carlos Paredes; Miguel Benitez, Julio Cesar Enciso, Carlos
Morales (Denis Caniza, 45th minute), Roberto Acuna; Jose Cardozo
(Cesar Ramirez 70), Jorge Campos (Juan Yegros, 77th).
	   Bulgaria_Zdravko Zdravkov; Radostin Kischishev, Trifon Ivanov,
Ivaylo Petkov, Zlatko Yankov; Krassimir Balakov, Ilian Iliev
(Daniel Borimirov, 80th), Anatoli Nankov, Ivaylo Iordanov; Hristo
Stoichkov, Luboslav Penev (Emil Kostadinov, 69th).
	   Referee_Abdul Rahman Al-Zeid, Saudi Arabia.
</TEXT>
