<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Armenia-Bus Fire </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Death toll in Armenian bus fire rises to six
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   YEREVAN, Armenia (AP) _ Two students died Friday from burns
suffered in a bus fire, bringing the death toll to six.
	   More than 20 people were badly burned when their bus, carrying
40 students, teachers and parents returning from a picnic, exploded
Sunday on a country road near the village of Bartsrashen, 30
kilometers (19 miles) south of Yerevan.
	   Officials said the explosion was apparently caused by a gas
leak.
	   Most buses and other vehicles in Armenia run on natural gas.
Gasoline is in short supply due to an economic blockade imposed by
neighboring Azerbaijan because of the two countries' territorial
conflict over Nagorno-Karabakh.
	   A teacher and three students remain in critical condition,
hospital officials said.
	   (str/ls) 	   
</TEXT>
