<HEADLINE>
Sophia Loren to star in Antonioni movie
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; AP Photos ROM-108, 109, 110

<TEXT>
	   ROME (AP) _ Sophia Loren and Oscar-winning director Michelangelo
Antonioni are planning a movie together, news reports said on
Friday.
	   ``It's an extraordinary role written especially for me,'' the
Italian actress was quoted by the ANSA news agency as saying.
	   ``You can't be sure until the first take,'' said Loren during a
visit to Rome. ``But it's an extraordinary project and I'll work
hard to get it done.''
	   The movie has the working title of ``Verna,'' Loren said.
	   The 85-year-old Antonioni, who directed ``Blow Up,'' ``Zabriskie
Point,'' and ``The Passenger'' has been hampered by the effects of
a stroke in recent years.
	   He last directed a movie in 1994, and won a lifetime Oscar award
in 1995.
	   (ar-cph)
</TEXT>
