	   IPOH, Wed. - Police arrested four men, an hour after they had
allegedly grabbed an undisclosed amount of money from an electrical
shop in Jalan Labrooy today.
	   A police party picked up the men while they were having drinks
at a roadside stall about 12.30pm.
	   An imitation police pistol, believed to have been used in the
robbery, was seized from one of them.
	   Prior to the arrest, the police had seized a taxi - believed to
have been used as a getaway vehicle following the robbery - which
was found abandoned in Jalan Kuala Kangsar.
	   Police are checking if two of the men were involved in robbing a
clinic of RM450, two gold chains and two rings, in Pasir Putih
yesterday.
	   In this morning's incident, two men, one carrying a ``pistol'',
walked into the electrical shop, held up an employee and fled with
an undislosed amount of money.
	   
