<HEADLINE>
NCR and Microsoft in networking products deal, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
NCR and Microsoft in networking products deal, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   NCR Corp has won a contract to provide third-party networking
products, installation and equipment maintenance support services
for 110 Microsoft Corp's offices in 62 international subsidiaries
across Asia, South America, Latin America, Europe and Africa.
	   NCR will be offering services and equipment to upgrade and
install Microsoft's new internal network architecture as part of an
initiative to improve the performance of Microsoft's Information
Technology Group's ability to deliver fast, high-quality service to
more than 30,000 global users.
	   As part of the network project, NCR will provide local
procurement, staging, export/import services, site surveys,
installation and acceptance testing, and on-site maintenance for
the deployment of Cisco networking products.
	   According to Microsoft's South Asia information technology (IT)
manager Bob Davis, NCR was chosen for its expertise as a network
integrator and its strong presence in Microsoft's key sites around
the world.
	   Davis said by leveraging on NCR's wide range of locations and
dedicated networking resources, Microsoft should be able to meet
the critical delivery dates for its network infrastructure, even in
hard-to-reach locations.
	   
</TEXT>
