<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Croatia accuses Jamaica of blocking access to training
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CHAUMONT, France (AP) - Croatian officials said that they plan
to protest to FIFA after being denied access to a Jamaican training
session Wednesday.
	   Jamaica denies the charge, claiming that the officials were in
fact journalists, and that the session was closed to foreign media.
	   ``The journalist was told on Tuesday that Wednesday night's
training session was not open to the foreign media, but he still
turned up and asked to be allowed in,'' said Ed Barnes, Jamaica's
spokesman.
	   Croatian officials insist that the man was a team
representative, but the Jamaicans say he was the same journalist
who had asked to attend the workout Tuesday.
	   Meanwhile, Jamaica has only one injury concern before its World
Cup opener against Croatia on Sunday.
	   Defender Frank Sinclair aggravated a groin injury and will
undergo a fitness test before the match.
	   (ae-sl)
