Witness: Sister threatened by motorist over parking lot, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Witness: Sister threatened by motorist over parking lot, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Wed. - A housewife told the Sessions Court today
that a motorist threatened to knock down her sister after the
latter refused to move from a vacant parking lot.
	   Koo May Chan, 33, said the man, who was standing outside his
car, was arguing with her sister Mei Fong while she (May Chan)
waited to park her car at the parking lot.
	   She said the man then got into his car and drove slowly towards
the parking lot and then suddenly knocked into Mei Fong and also
those waiting with her.
	   May Chan said those waiting with Mei Fong at the vacant parking
lot were the latter's two children, who were in a trolley, and also
her own children.
	   She was giving evidence at the trial of businessman Teh Chuan
Ann, 40, who is charged with attempting to commit culpable homicide
not amounting to murder of Mei Fong, Chiew Yuen Kee and Chin Sim
Yee.
	   Teh, of Taman Tenaga, Cheras, is alleged to have committed the
offence on Jan 25 this year, about 7.30pm at the Jaya Jusco
supermarket car park in Taman Maluri, Cheras.
	   He claimed trial to the charge as well as two charges of
committing mischief by causing damage of above RM25 to the two
vehicles at the same place and time.
	   May Chan said after the incident she rushed out of her car
towards the parking lot to see whether her children were still
alive.
	   She said she saw someone pulling out Chiew, who is Mei Fong's
daughter, from under the car and her body and face were covered
with blood.
	   May Chan said her daughter Chin, was also pulled out from under
the car and she had injuries on her legs.
	   She said the family had gone to Jaya Jusco and upon reaching the
car park Mei Fong and the children stepped out of the car.
	   May Chan said Mei Fong took a trolley that was in front the car
and went to the vacant parking lot with the children.
	   She said she then saw a blue Proton Wira passing on her right
and heading towards the same parking lot.
	   Hearing before judge Lim Yee Lan continues.
	   
</TEXT>
