	   AN UNUSUAL GARDEN ... In the midst of chaotic traffic that marks
Jalan Stadium in Alor Star lies this patch planted with ginger,
serai, lengkuas, pegaga, sireh, sweet potato, tapioca and
pineapple.
	   This roundabout actually serves as a vegetable plot or rather a
herbal garden.
	   The unlikely garden was an idea mooted by Menteri Besar Tan Sri
Sanusi Junid in an effort to landscape the town and popularise the
idea of edible gardens.
	   The roundabout was planted with several kinds of vegetables,
herbs and plants in early 1997 and is maintained by the Kota Setar
Municipal Council at the cost of about RM1,000 a month.
	   The garden was first harvested last week with its yield sold to
council staff and members of the public for a cool RM1,200.
	   A council spokesman said the plants were harvested every four to
six months depending on its type.
	   The spokesman said that maintenance however was a difficult job.
	   
