<HEADLINE>
Family of 11 shot to death
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AMMAN, Jordan (AP) _ Police arrested a man Friday on charges he
killed 11 members of his family in a killing spree that shocked
Jordan.
	   Police said Saeed Qashash, 18, confessed that he killed his
family because he feared he might fail his high school exams.
	   Police did not say if he had any accomplices.
	   The dead included school bus driver Amin Qashash, 50, his wife,
four children, a son-in-law and four grandchildren. They were
killed before dawn Thursday in their home in Banayat, a village 20
kilometers (12 miles) northwest of Amman, government officials
said. Qashash is Amin Quashash's son.
	   The family was shot in their house's basement and a brick wall
was then built to hide its entrance, an official said, speaking on
condition of anonymity.
	   A quiet country with a reputation for security, Jordan has been
shaken recently by a series of shootings and bombings. 	   
