<HEADLINE>
Paul McCartney approves plans to name cancer unit after wife
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LIVERPOOL, England (AP) _ Former Beatle Paul McCartney has given
his consent to plans to name a new cancer center after his wife,
Linda, who died of breast cancer last month.
	   The center, which will cost 4 million pounds (dlrs 6.5 million),
is scheduled to open next spring in this northwest England city,
which gave birth to the Fab Four _ and where McCartney grew up.
	   ``We are delighted to honor the memory of Lady Linda in this way
and are so pleased that her name is to be associated with a
development that will be of undoubted benefit to patients from Sir
Paul's hometown,'' said Keith Parsons, chief executive of the Royal
Liverpool University Hospitals, where the center will be based.
	   An appeal campaign in memory of Mrs. McCartney that has been set
up to fund the center currently stands at 3.2 million pounds (dlrs
5 million).
	   (jh-kg)
