	   WORLD AT 1700 GMT:
	   NEW:
	   _SUDAN-FIGHTING-OIL. Rebels claim capture of strategic town.
	   _KOSOVO-WAR CRIMES. War crimes tribunal sending investigators to
Kosovo.
	   _US-CHINA: America needs China as ally, ambassador says.
	   _WORLD CUP-MARSEILLE MANIA. Football only concern for all races.
 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia _ Ethnic Albanian militants, boldly
stepping up their attacks, kill two Serb policemen just a few miles
(kilometers) from Kosovo's capital and say Friday that they command
15,000 fighters across the secessionist province.
YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO. Lead has moved to some points, upcoming
elsewhere. By Ismet Hajdari. AP Photos BAJ101-103.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _NATO-KOSOVO. NATO and Russia agree on danger, differ on method.
AP Photos BRU101-105.
	   _FOREIGN MINISTERS. G-7 plus Russia grapple with Kosovo, agree
on new sanctions for India, Pakistan. AP Photos LON109, 111, 113,
119.
	   _KOSOVO-WAR CRIMES. U.N. war crimes tribunal to send
investigators to Kosovo.
	   LAGOS, Nigeria _ Troops firing into the air, riot police at the
ready with tear gas, Nigeria's new military boss sends a clear
signal to his opponents Friday: Muscle still rules this junta-weary
country. NIGERIA. Lead has moved. By Tim Sullivan.
	   LISBON, Portugal _ Tens of thousands of people flee the former
Portuguese colony of Guinea-Bissau on Friday as government troops
fight renegade soldiers who launched a coup attempt. GUINEA BISSAU.
Lead has moved. By Barry Hatton.
	   ADIGRAT, Ethiopia _ The guns are quiet in the Ethiopia-Eritrea
conflict Friday, but the two governments continue their salvos of
accusations. ETHIOPIA-ERITREA. Has moved to some points, upcoming
elsewhere. By Dianna Cahn. AP Photos ADI101-104.
	   NEW DELHI, India _ India says it and Pakistan agree Friday to
resume top-level talks, but Pakistan's foreign minister denies it,
dashing hopes of an imminent reversal of the escalating tension
since both countries joined the nuclear club.
INDIA-PAKISTAN-NUCLEAR. Lead has moved. By Arthur Max.
	   BOMBAY, India _ The cyclone that killed at least 735 people
forces poor villagers in western India to take to the roads Friday
in search of food and water. INDIA-CYCLONE. Lead has moved. By
Ramola Talwar. AP Photo BOM107.
	   TOKYO _ For nearly a year, Asia has been looking to Japan to
lead the troubled region back to prosperity. But with Friday's news
that Japan is in recession, the world's second largest economy
looks like more of a liability than a potential savior.
JAPAN-RECESSION. Lead has moved. By Joji Sakurai.
	   WASHINGTON _ China's ambassador suggests that the democratic
United States needs communist China as an ally in a region troubled
by nuclear threats and financial crisis. US-CHINA. Expected by 2000
GMT. By Laura Myers. AP Photo WX104.
	   NAIROBI, Kenya _ Southern Sudan rebels say Friday that they have
captured a strategic town in the Blue Nile province and warn
foreign oil companies it will not honor their exploration
concessions there. SUDAN-FIGHTING-OIL. Has moved. By Chege Mbitiru.
	   MARSEILLE, France _ The people shouting, ``Go France,'' include
Algerians just off the boat, kids of Senegalese descent, and
right-wing whites who in normal times say Arabs and blacks should
go home. WORLD CUP-MARSEILLE MANIA. Has moved. Lead expected after
game begins at 1900 GMT. By Mort Rosenblum. AP Photos XWCMA101,
105-108.
	   JERUSALEM _ Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu meets with the
leader of the opposition Friday amid reports that a unity
government might be under consideration. ISRAEL-PALESTINIANS. Lead
has moved. By Dina Kraft.
	   CAPE TOWN, South Africa _ The United States and Britain asked
the apartheid government to withhold its biological warfare
technology from the majority black government that was expected to
succeed it, a panel hears Friday. SOUTH AFRICA-APARTHEID PLOT. Lead
expected by 1900 GMT. By Paul Harris. AP Photos CPN101-103.
	   FLINT, Michigan _ By this time next week, a labor dispute may
shut down the vast North American operation of the world's No. 1
automaker. US-GM STRIKE. Lead has moved. By Brian S. Akre. AP
Photos XFLI101-103, TRE101.
	   ALSO MOVED: US-COMPAQ-DIGITAL. Compaq cutting 2,000 jobs as it
absorbs newly acquired Digital.
	   LAS MARGARITAS, Mexico _ With fears of renewed war between
Zapatista rebels and the government, Mexico's president flies to
Chiapas to defend his administration's stated desire for dialogue.
MEXICO-CHIAPAS. Lead expected by 1900 GMT. By Niko Price. AP Photos
pursuing.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: Queensland state elections in Australia are
Saturday. A two-day European Union summit starts Monday in Cardiff,
Wales.
