<SLUG> BC-Russia-Fire </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Fire breaks out on gas pipeline
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A fire broke out on a gas pipeline in the Perm
region of Russia and spread into a nearby forest, the ITAR-Tass
news agency said Friday.
	   Flames shot 100 meters (yards) into the air from the
Urengoi-Uzhgorod gas pipeline near the village of Mazuyevka, about
1,125 kilometers (700 miles) west of Moscow.
	   The pipeline appeared to have been leaking gas before the fire
started, but the cause was not known, ITAR-Tass said.
	   The flow of gas was stopped, but the fire still spread over 5
hectares (12 acres) of forest, it said.
	   (ls) 	   
