EDs: LEADS with closing figures
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; London shares fall as rally fizzles &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Prices gave up early gains and plunged to fresh
losses Friday on the London Stock Exchange.
	   Dealers blamed heavy selling in the futures market and a gloomy
attitude brought about by big drops on Wall Street.
	   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 82.7
points, or 1.4 percent, to 5,769.8.
	   Provisional volume came to 822 million shares, compared with 950
million shares in Thursday's session.
