<SLUG> BC-Romania-US </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Romania, US hope to increase cooperation
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) _ In an effort to increase cooperation,
a group of Romanian and U.S. representatives agreed on 18 projects
Friday designed to boost investment and security in Romania.
	   ``All these projects aim to promote Romania's economic and
security interests,'' the Mediafax news agency quoted former U.S.
Defense Secretary William Perry as saying.
	   Among the most important projects is a plan to create a fund to
aid small and medium companies in Romania.
	   Other proposed projects focus on areas such as agriculture,
banking, telecommunications, energy and foreign policy. They will
be submitted to the governments of both countries for adoption.
	   The group started its work Thursday. Next week, the American
delegation is set to meet with President Emil Constantinescu and
Prime Minister Radu Vasile.
	   Constantinescu said Romania needs more American investment and
pleaded in a press conference for ``consistent U.S. economic and
financial support.''
	   (ma/scl)
