	   MORE than 120 participants who attended the Malaysia British
Assurance Regional Marketing Convention at the Regency Hotel in
Port Dickson, Negri Sembilan, recently not only enjoyed the weekend
but also pooled their resources for a worthy cause.
	   Agents from Negri Sembilan, Malacca and Johor enjoyed a variety
of stage shows and games.
	   However, they did not forget the less fortunate and raised
RM1,140 to assist six-year-old Al-Zikri Abdul Karim whose plight
was highlighted in the New Straits Times on May 21.
	   Al-Zikri needs RM25,000 for surgery to correct severe breathing
difficulties caused by a complex congenital heart lesion.
	   The surgery is to be held at the Ampang Puteri Hospital.
	   MBA regional manager (southern branch) Gan Chin Chia said the
money was raised from the sale of tickets for their hamper lucky
draw.
	   He said it was the least the agents could do to assist the less
fortunate.
	   The cheque was presented by an agent K.K. Lim who won the lucky
draw that night, to New Straits Times journalist Patrick Sennyah.
	   Lim was accompanied by Gan and MBA general manager Mei York
Liang.
	   
