<SLUG> BC-Britain-German Gaffe </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
German flag taken down at EU summit site due to misspelling
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CARDIFF, Wales (AP) _ A huge flag hanging outside City Hall to
mark Germany's participation in the upcoming European Union summit
was taken down Friday after eagle-eyed Germans noticed
``Deutschland'' was misspelled on it.
	   The 30-foot-high (9-meter-high) banner instead spelled it
``Deutchsland.''
	   German Chancellor Helmut Kohl is among the European heads of
government arriving this weekend for the gathering in the Welsh
capital.
	   Flags from all 15 participating nations had been hoisted outside
City Hall, which will serve as the main summit venue.
	   ``We have now removed the banner and will be replacing it as
soon as possible,'' said a spokeswoman for the British Foreign
Office, speaking on condition of anonymity. ``We apologized and are
grateful that the mistake was spotted''.
	   But the error left at least one German fuming.
	   ``This is absolutely pathetic,'' said Jorg Mathias, a lecturer
at Cardiff University. ``It just goes to show when it comes to
Europe, they don't know what they're talking about. The summit
should never have been held here in the first place if they can't
get a simple thing like the spelling of a country right''.
	   (kg)
</TEXT>
