	   KUALA LUMPUR, Wed. - Rampant unauthorised cash withdrawals have
prompted Perwira Affin Bank to change the personal identification
numbers of all its Cinta cardholders.
	   The exercise, which started on Monday and is on-going, will
involve about 350,000 Cinta automated teller machine cardholders.
	   PAB general manager for corporate services Yusof A. Zain said
today the exercise was necessary to safeguard the customers'
interests.
	   The move is also in line with Bank Negara's recommendations to
curb illegal withdrawals.
	   Cinta cardholders may change their PIN immediately at any Cinta
ATMs.
	   Cardholders will be updated on the changes through the ATM
screens, Cinta ATM transaction receipts, current account statements
and notices posted on MEPS ATMs.
	   For more information contact 1-800-88-3883 or 03-264 3660/3617
or PAB's customer service executives.
	   
