<HEADLINE>
Pact on multimedia courses, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Pact on multimedia courses, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   OPENG Technologies has entered into an agreement with Edith
Cowan University (ECU) of Perth, Western Australia, and Prism Group
Pty Ltd to deliver comprehensive and world-class multimedia courses
in Malaysia.
	   Under the agreement, Gopeng Technologies will be responsible for
setting up computer laboratory centres nationwide which will be
equipped with state-of-the-art equipment designed to deliver
multimedia courses.
	   ECU will provide expert tuition in project management,
interface, graphics and instructional design, programming, online
learning via the Internet, and all forms of digital media.
	   Gopeng Technologies' group general manager Adnan Zainal said the
alliance will strengthen the group's ability to provide world-class
education programmes based on multimedia technologies.
	   He added that Gopeng Technologies will be establishing a number
of alliances with Government-approved educational institutions
throughout the country over the next two years to provide greater
access to the courses.
	   According to ECU's vice chancellor Professor Millicent Poole,
multimedia is a booming industry which has the potential to
contribute substantially to the Malaysian economy.
	   The courses that will be offered under the agreement are
Executive/Graduate Certificate (Interactive Multimedia
Technologies), Executive/Graduate Diploma (Interactive Multimedia
Technologies), and Master of Arts (Interactive Multimedia
Technologies).
	   
</TEXT>
