<HEADLINE>
At least eight die in Turkish floods
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SANLIURFA, Turkey (AP) _ At least eight people died Friday when
they were swept away by floods driven by torrential rains in a
village in this southeastern province, officials said.
	   Up to 20 other people were missing, feared drowned in rushing
rainwater in the village of Gozeli, village alderman Cuma Gocmen
told ATV television. Six of the dead were students on an outing
near the village, he said.
	   Sanliurfa is some 820 kilometers (490 miles) southeast of the
capital, Ankara.
	   Last month, floods sweeping northwestern Turkey killed some 20
people, inundated thousands of homes and destroyed bridges, roads
and railway lines.
	   (sf)
