	   HE Johor Government have requested that the name of the Tiger
Cup soccer tournament scheduled to be held at the Larkin Stadium in
August to be changed to the Asean Football Federation Cup.
	   The State Executive Councillor for Sports Dr Abdul Latiff Ahmad
yesterday said: ``We have got nothing against the tournament but
since it is connected with an alcoholic drink, we have to be
sensitive to the feelings of certain quarters in the State.
	   ``That's why the State Government would be grateful if the
organisers can change it to the AFF Cup.''
	   
