	   USTRALIAN Steve Darby is to take over from K. Sukumaran as coach
of the Johor Premier Two team.
	   The 44-year old Darby, who has vast experience in Australian
including a five-year stint as a development officer with the
Australian Soocer Federation and also an assistant coach at the top
club, Sydney Olympic, is expected to arrive in Johor Baru today.
	   His appointment was announced by the Johor FA president Datuk
Mohammad Ali Hashim yesterday, three days after Sukumaran was
relieved of his duties following the team's dismal run in the
league.
	   And for the past three days, including last night's FA Cup tie
against Perlis, Johor FC coach Ronald Smith was roped in to help
out.
	   ``Darby's appointment will be for six months and he will work
closely with Smith,'' said Ali.
	   Johor FA had decided last week that Sukumaran will be asked to
take a rest while they scout around for a new coach, a man with
vast experience and who can provide a new approach.
	   It was also decided that the Australian forward Bob Ivanstanin
who had a week-long trial with Johor, is not the player they wanted
to shore up their forwardline.
	   Ivanstanin was tried out training sessions and a few friendly
matches and team officials decided that he did not fit the bill.
	   
</TEXT>
