	   YOGYAKARTA: Sri Roso Sudarmo, who was temporarily removed as
Bantul regent Wednesday, vehemently denied yesterday that he was
involved in the highly publicized 1996 murder of Bernas daily's
journalist Fuad Muhammad Syafruddin, alias Udin.
	   ``How am I supposed defend myself anymore? Of course I deny it
(the allegation),'' Sri Roso told reporters after surrendering his
post to Governor Paku Alam III.
	   He urged people to presume he was innocent unless a legal
process could prove otherwise.
	   The slain journalist was known to be investigating corruption in
the Bantul area when he was murdered.
	   ``So, don't accuse me carelessly. This is not a defense, but
please give me a chance to prove my innocence,'' he said.
	   Sri Roso was formally discharged due to public pressure on the
government to investigate him after evidence was uncovered that he
offered a Rp 1 billion ``donation'' to a Soeharto-owned fund in
exchange for a second term.
	   
