<HEADLINE>
Chance for Penang to gauge standard, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Chance for Penang to gauge standard, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Lee Keng FattASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   OW far last year's losing finalists Penang will go in the FA Cup
this year will be known on Saturday when they meet Sabah in the
Premier One League clash at the Likas Stadium.
	   For that's when they get to gauge their ability against Sabah,
whom they will meet by the luck of draw, on June 23 in the FA Cup
quarterfinals.
	   But for now, Penang will savour their 3-1 FA Cup second round
second leg win over Pahang at the Darulmakmur Stadium on Tuesday,
the first time the Premier One leaders have been beaten at their
home turf.
	   Perhaps this explains why Penang coach Moey Yoke Ham is
confident about about his team making headway again.
	   ``The victory over Pahang has given us the much needed
confidence. It was a good result. It augurs well for our future
matches, especially the two away matches against Sabah.
	   ``We can now take on Sabah with much confidence.''
	   Moey's previous misgivings about the team's performance was
understandable as Penang's morale was affected following their two
straight defeats to Kedah two weeks ago.
	   That was until they popped in a late goal in their win against
Negri Sembilan at home last Saturday.
	   Then came the victory over Pahang on Tuesday in the FA Cup.
	   ``Hopefully, we will be able to repeat the way we performed in
last season's FA Cup. However, I'd rather take each match at a
time,'' said Moey.
	   Against Sabah, Penang will have to do without defender Zaidi Mat
Ail who is out after two yellow cards and the injured newcomer in
defence, Nordin Kamis, who is down with a hamstring pull.
	   Defender Rahim Hassan, who has just recovered from a muscular
pull, and midfielder Ng Kok Heng who out out on a one-match
suspension, will make a return to the team.
	   
</TEXT>
