Meet Borhan, the fiercely patriotic fruit seller, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Meet Borhan, the fiercely patriotic fruit seller, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   PATRIOTISM ... Meet Borhan Namat, 45, who sells various kinds of
fruits.
	   What's so special about that?
	   Well, the trader from Taman Pauh Indah, Bukit Mertajam, has been
selling only local fruits for the last 15 years, long before the
``Buy Malaysian''
	   campaign.
	   Even though he can earn extra money by selling imported fruits
such as apples and oranges alongside Malaysian fruits, Borhan has
not done so.
	   Therefore, it is no surprise that during the current durian
season he sells only local or kampung durians which he gets from
Batu Kurau in Perak. He refuses to sell the Thai varieties.
	   NST photographer Kamil Rahim spotted Borhan at his makeshift
stall in Taman Chai Leng, Prai, yesterday.
	   ``The types of fruits I sell depend on the season. They include
watermelon, papaya, mango or jackfruit,'' said Borhan.
	   
</TEXT>
