<HEADLINE>
Four men hijack lorry on highway, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Four men hijack lorry on highway, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUANTAN, Wed. - Four men, one armed with a knife, hijacked a
lorry laden with a consignment of Nestle products worth about
RM80,000, at Km52 of the Kuala Lumpur-Karak Highway early
yesterday.
	   The vehicle, which was heading towards Kuantan from Shah Alam,
was hijacked when its driver and assistant stopped for a rest near
Bukit Tinggi about 2am.
	   Four men, who arrived in a car overpowered the two men before
tying them with ropes.
	   State Criminal Investigation Department chief Assistant
Commissioner Sulaiman Mahmud said today two of the four drove the
driver and his assistant in their car towards Selangor while the
rest drove off with the lorry.
	   He said the victims were released unharmed at an oil palm estate
in Jalan Meru, Klang.
	   Sulaiman urged those who knew the whereabouts of the hijacked
Mercedes Benz lorry, bearing registration number TN4333, to contact
the nearest police station.
	   
