<HEADLINE>
Iranians willing to assist Malaysia, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Iranians willing to assist Malaysia, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KOTA BARU, Wed. - The Iranian Government today expressed its
willingness to assist the Malaysian Government in overcoming its
economic problem.
	   Its ambassador to Malaysia Hossein Sereydoun said a special
envoy representing the Iranian Government would be in Kuala Lumpur
next week to meet Deputy Prime Minister Datuk Seri Anwar Ibrahim to
discuss the matter.
	   The envoy would also meet Bank Negara governor Tan Sri Ahmad
Mohd Don and Foreign Minister Datuk Seri Abdullah Ahmad Badawi,
Hossein added.
	   ``The meeting will cover among others, ways the Iranian
Government can assist the Malaysia overcome its economic
problems,'' he told reporters after a courtesy call on Menteri
Besar Datuk Nik Abdul Aziz Nik Mat at his official residence.
	   He said the outcome of the discussion with the Malaysian leaders
would be conveyed to President Ayatollah Khatami who will decide on
the form of assistance to Malaysia.
	   
