<HEADLINE>
Rioch named coach at Norwich
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Bruce Rioch is back coaching English soccer again
after being named Friday to coach division one side Norwich.
	   The 51-year-old former Arsenal and Bolton boss has been without
a manager's job since he was dumped by Queens Park Rangers as
assistant manager in November.
	   Norwich chairman Barry Lockwood confirmed Rioch would link with
his former Everton teammate Bryan Hamilton, who is the new director
of football at Carrow Road.
	   Lockwood said he was delighted that both Rioch and Hamilton.
	   ``We feel their appointments will create an environment of
ambition within the club both in the dressing room and the
stands,'' he said.
	   Rioch said he planned to use a new approach at Norwich.
	   ``There is a great deal of work for us to do. But the great
saying I've been brought up with has been, `There is no I in
teamwork.' We must work together,'' he said.
	   (jp)	   
