	   KUCHING, Wed. - Mutiara Telecom today donated two handphones to
the Sibu Kidney Association to help facilitate the latter's daily
operations.
	   Its regional manager (East Malaysia) Wee Hong Guap handed over
the phones, which comes with RM150 worth of prepaid cards each, to
the association's treasurer Datuk Wong Soon Koh at Wisma Bapa
Malaysia today.
	   Wong, who is also State Minister for Infrastructure Development
and Communications, commended Mutiara Telecom for their donation
and urged other firms to emulate it.
	   Wee said the donation formed part of his company's social
obligations.
	   Earlier this year, Mutiara Telecom had contributed prepaid cards
worth about RM100,000 to the National Kidney Foundation.
	   
