<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Iran,0264 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Iranian coach announces roster for game with Yugoslavia
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By ANWAR FARUQI &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   YSSINGEAUX, France (AP) _ Iran's coach Jalal Talebi said Friday
he hopes to put the same players in the World Cup game with
Yugoslavia as he did in a warm-up match with Croatia earlier this
month.
	   Iran lost 2-0 to Croatia, but Talebi said his team had played
well. He said he was using the same players because Croatian soccer
was similar to Yugoslavia's.
	   It all depends on injury problems.
	   Talebi said that his goalkeeper and captain, Ahmad Reza
Abedzadeh, could have to miss Sunday's game at St. Etienne because
he still had not recuperated from a knee operation late last year.
	   Meanwhile, midfielder Reza Shahroudi was carried off the field
with an injury to his left leg during a practice match Friday.
Fellow midfielder Sattar Hamedani walked off the field with an ice
pack on his leg, as he did on Wednesday.
	   Iran is expected to adopt a defensive strategy against the
formidable Yugoslav attackers. But Abedzadeh's absence and possible
injuries that could keep out key players, may make Iran's weak
defense even weaker.
	   Talebi, who took over the team less than a month ago, used the
following opening roster in the June 3 game against Croatia in
Rijeka:
	   Nima Nakissa, Javad Zarincheh, Nader Mohammadkhani, Mehdi
Pashazadeh, Mohammad Khakpour, Karim Bagheri, Mehdi Mahdavikia,
Reza Shahroudi, Khodadad Azizi, Ali Daei, Hamid Reza Estili.
