<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Italy,0496 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Baggio-Del Piero together?
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By PIERO VALSECCHI &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   SENLIS, France (AP) _ With Roberto Baggio in top form and
Alessandro Del Piero ready to return on the team, coach Cesare
Maldini on Friday was thinking the unthinkable.
	   Can the two Italian star-forwards play together?
	   A heresy until a few days ago, the possibility of starting the
former Juventus teammates in Wednesday's match against Cameroon was
being considered. This year, the two scored a total of 43 goals on
different teams.
	   ``I must understand if they can play together, and in which way.
I have several days for deciding, before the next match,'' Maldini
said at Italy's training camp in Senlis following a dramatic 2-2
draw against Chile at Bordeaux.
	   Baggio, a 31-year-old veteran on his third World Cup, was taken
to France as Del Piero's substitute and fielded against Chile
because the younger teammate still is in questionable form
following a right thigh strain.
	   Baggio was the best player on the Italian side in Bordeaux and
salvaged Italy from a sensational upset by earning and converting a
late penalty.
	   ``I fielded only one of them (against Chile) because the other
had physical problems ... I don't know if they are compatible. I'll
think of it. I had thought of this also before the World Cup,''
Maldini said.
	   Italy may need to field a third forward against the African team
in Montpellier as Baggio and Christian Vieri looked quite isolated
in front against Chile.
	   ``That was a tactical problem (against the Chileans). We must
improve cohesion between midfield and the attack,'' the Italian
coach explained.
	   He rejected criticism of young defenders Alessandro Nesta and
Fabio Cannavaro, who had a difficult match against Ivan Zamorano
and Marcelo Salas in Thursday's match of Group B.
	   Salas scored both Chile's goals while Zamorano was a steady
threat with his headers.
	   ``Zamorano is one of the best world players in aerial play and
is difficult to stop. I can say both Nesta and Cannavaro will start
against Cameroon,'' Maldini said.
	   ``We are aware that Cameroon is very strong athletically. We
will study the tape of its last match against Austria tonight,'' he
said.
	   Del Piero, 23, practiced full time Friday and said he felt ready
to play against Cameroon.
	   ``It's up to Maldini to decide if I can be started. I am ready.
I see no problem in playing with three forwards, along with Roberto
(Baggio),'' Del Piero said.
	   Following the first round of matches all Group B teams have one
point from draws. Austria and Cameroon played to a 1-1 tie Thursday
night.
	   Maldini said Italy will have to play for victory against
Cameroon.
	   ``We also played for victory against Chile. I personally believe
we were unlucky as we had ten shots at the net compared with
Chile's only two,'' the coach added.
	   (pv-sl)
</TEXT>
