<HEADLINE>
Primary pupils to take part in art contest, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Primary pupils to take part in art contest, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   WITH the Commonwealth Games fast approaching, Sukom Ninety Eight
Berhad in collaboration with the Education Ministry and Nestle
Products Sdn Bhd, is organising an art competition for primary
schoolchildren in the Klang Valley.
	   Entitled Kuala Lumpur `98 Sukan Komanwel XVI - Malaysia Boleh,
the competition will be held on Aug 9 at the indoor stadium,
National Sports Complex, Bukit Jalil.
	   The event was launched by Deputy Education Minister and chief de
mission of the Malaysian Commonwealth Games contingent Datuk Khalid
Yunus at Sukom Ninety Eighty's headquarters in Serdang recently.
	   The company's chief operating officer Lt-Jen (Rtd) Datuk Seri
Abdul Manap Ibrahim said between 6,000 and 8,000 children from
government and private schools are expected to take part.
	   ``It is aimed at making children aware of the Games and presents
an opportunity for the children and their parents to see the new
sports complex,'' he said.
	   Abdul Manap said the competition has two sections - category A
for Standard One to Three students and category B for Standard Four
and Six.
	   ``The school with the largest participation will receive a cash
prize of RM1,000,'' he added. ``All participating students will
receive a certificate.''
	   He added that Datin Seri Dr siti Hasmah Mohd Ali, wife of the
Prime Minister, will give away the prizes to 50 winners.
	   The art competition is sponsored by Genting Theme Park, Wira
Club and Faber Castell which will provide the art materials.
	   
