<HEADLINE>
Advisory,0277
</HEADLINE>

BULLETIN-IMMEDIATE BROADCAST REQUESTED
URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY
NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE SAN JUAN PR
306 PM AST FRI JUN 12 1998


...THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE IN SAN JUAN PR HAS ISSUED AN URBAN
   AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY EFFECTIVE UNTIL 600 PM FOR
   NORTHWEST  PUERTO RICO...

...INCLUDING THE MUNICIPALITIES OF ARECIBO...HATILLO...CAMUY...
QUEBRADILLAS...ISABELLA...AGUADILLA...SAN SEBASTIAN AND MOCA...

DOPPLER RADAR INDICATED SHOWERS AND THUNDERSTORMS WITH TORRENTIAL
RAIN FROM THE WESTERN HALF OF ARECIBO ACROSS TO AGUADILLA AND
INLAND TO PORTIONS OF MOCA AND SAN SEBASTIAN. THESE SHOWERS WILL
TRACK TOWARD THE WEST NORTHWEST AND PRODUCE FLOODING OF STREETS...
STREAMS AND LOW LYING AREAS ACROSS PLACES IN THE ABOVE
MUNICIPALITIES.

BE ESPECIALLY CAREFUL ACROSS THE MUNICIPALITES OF AGUADILLA...MOCA...
AND BETWEEN ARECIBO AND HATILLO WHERE DOPPLER RADAR ESTIMATED NEAR 4
INCHES OF RAIN THIS PAST HOUR. CIVIL DEFENSE REPORTED FLOODING
ACROSS THE CORALES SECTOR IN AGUADILLA. THEREFORE AN URBAN AND SMALL
STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY WILL REMAIN IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM...AT WHICH
TIME THE SHOWERS WILL DISSIPATE ACROSS THIS AREA.

MOTORISTS AND PEDESTRIANS IN OR PASSING THROUGH THE NORTHWEST FROM
ARECIBO WEST TO AGUADILLA...ESPECIALLY ON OR ALONG HIGHWAY 2...
SHOULD AVOID CROSSING FLOODED ROADS... AND ALLOW EXTRA
TIME TO REACH THEIR DESTINATIONS. REMEMBER...CARS CAN EASILY STALL
IN THE WATER AND BE CARRIED AWAY IN ANY CURRENT. PEDESTRIANS ARE
ALSO ADVISED TO STAY AWAY FROM RISING CREEKS.
 &HT;    
