<HEADLINE>
Nature at its best in Negri forest, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Nature at its best in Negri forest, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Siti Rahmah LehanASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE Lenggeng Recreational Forest is among the destinations to be
promoted during Visit Negri Sembilan Year 1999.
	   A Negri Sembilan Forestry Department spokesman said the forest
comprised virgin jungle with wildlife and flora.
	   It also has majestic outcrops of granite.
	   The spokesman said the area has facilities such as wooden
bridges, camping grounds, park benches, wooden huts and pergolas.
	   He said the forest offers rivers with crystal-clear waters, and
cascading waterfalls.
	   He said among the complaints received from the public was the
absence of a hawker centre and public toilet.
	   ``The reason we do not construct a hawker centre here is because
of the littering problem.
	   ``We are also having a problem with water supply which makes it
difficult for us to have public toilets,'' he said.
	   Located near Km8 Jalan Pantai Lenggeng, the forest is only half
an hour's journey from Seremban town.
	   Among the rare attractions at the forest are the rare species of
flowers, insects and wild orchids with unique shapes and sweet
smell.
	   Nature lovers keen on jungle trekking will be impressed by the
extraordinary shapes and sizes of the rocks which border the river.
	   The forest reserve has also become a favourite spot for the
older generation to exercise and appreciate the fresh air.
	   However, for those who wish to visit the place, personal
transport must be arranged as there was no public transport service
there.
	   The Forestry spokesman said if the promotion was to be a
success, efforts must be made to enable easy access via public
transport.
	   He said the department was also planning to build a public
toilet and provide more litter bins.
	   
</TEXT>
