	   RATING Agency Malaysia (RAM) Bhd has revised the short-term
rating of Kesas Sdn Bhd's RM422.5 million guaranteed revolving
underwritten notes issuance facility (Grunif) 1994/2008 to P2(s)
from P2.
	   The rating reflects Kesas' ultimate shareholders' commitment to
provide funds in the form of equity or loan to enable the company
to maintain a debt service coverage ratio of 1.25 times, throughout
the tenure of the Grunif.
	   The ratio is higher than the minimum 1.05 times required under
the facilities agreement, and the resolution to inject funds by
three of the four shareholders is therefore a critical element in
supporting the rating, RAM said in a statement.
	   Kesas is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Kesas Holdings Bhd, which
in turn is jointly owned by Gamuda Bhd, Percon Corp Sdn Bhd, Arab
Malaysian Development Bhd and Perbadanan Kemajuan Negeri Selangor.
	   However, RAM said it is unable to comment on the possible extent
of credit enhancement since the RM422.5 million Grunif is
unconditionally and irrevocably guaranteed by a consortium of
financial institutions which include unrated financial
institutions.
	   
