WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SPK-Sentosa Corporation Bhd sank deeper into the red by
recording a group pre-tax loss of RM8.42 million for the year ended
Dec 31, 1997 from a loss of RM1.79 million previously. Turnover at
the group level, however, increased to RM35 million from RM21
million, said the company. At the company level, it incurred a
pre-tax loss of RM9.66 million from a loss of RM2.43 million while
turnover declined to RM8.9 million for the period under review from
RM14.2 million earlier. The lower turnover was due to the
discontinued operations of the plywood factory in the third quarter
of the year as a result of the unfavourable market conditions and
the continuing losses. SPK-Sentosa, however, said prospects for the
current year were favourable.
	   
</TEXT>
