	   IPOH, Thurs. - The State Government should gazette land for
vegetable cultivation and cattle rearing to ensure adequate supply
of food.
	   People's Progressive Party national vice-chairman A. Ayyathurai
said some farmers and breeders were facing uncertainties because
they were using land which they only had temporary occupation
licences.
	   ``They are not willing to invest heavily on their farms as they
fear the Government might take back the land for development,'' he
added.
	   He expressed fear that food supply in the State would be
adversely affected if more such land was developed.
	   
