MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUANTAN, Thurs. - The State Government plans to make use of
ex-mining pools and idle padi fields for fish breeding in its
effort to boost food production.
	   Menteri Besar Tan Sri Mohd Khalil Yaakob said today the State
Government had identified numerous sites with a total area of
4,000ha for this purpose.
	   ``Once implemented, these projects are capable of supplying
36,087 tonnes of fish annually,'' he said.
	   He said 70 former mining sites would be used. Of the number, 22
are located here, 20 in Raub, 17 in Lipis, 10 in Bera and one in
Maran.
	   ``The State Government will aggressively promote aquaculture,''
he told reporters after launching a nasi padang promotion at Hotel
Seri Malaysia yesterday.
	   Also present were his deputy Datuk Hasan Arifin, State executive
councillors and State Secretary Datuk Abdul Ghani Sulaiman and
other senior State Government officers.
	   
</TEXT>
