<HEADLINE>
Intan to sell 17.8pc equity to CGE, BUSINESS TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Intan to sell 17.8pc equity to CGE, BUSINESS TIMES &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Vasantha GanesanASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   INTAN Utilities Bhd's substantial shareholders - Vista Meranti
Sdn Bhd and its wholly-owned subsidiary IMD Sdn Bhd - has proposed
to sell 9.55 million shares of RM1 each representing 17.84 per cent
of the issued and paid-up capital of Intan to Compagnie Generale
Des Eaux Asia Pacific Pte Ltd (CGE Asia Pacific).
	   Tan Sri Vincent Tan Chee Yioun, the ultimate controlling
shareholder of Vista and IMD, is deemed interested in a further
10.8 per cent stake in Intan by virtue of his majority interest in
Berjaya Group Bhd, which also have investments in Intan.
	   Following the sale, Vista's and IMD's collective stake in Intan
will be reduced to 21.01 per cent whilst Tan will have 31.81 per
cent equity interest in Intan.
	   In the meantime, CGE Asia Pacific has contracted to purchase up
to 30.0 per cent equity interest in Intan from Vista, IMD and other
third parties.
	   Vista and IMD will innovate the operation and maintanence
agreement, corporate management agreement and project management
agreement to Kristal Utama Sdn Bhd which will be a 75 per cent
owned subsidiary company of CGE Asia Pacific and 25 per cent owned
by Vista.
	   Meanwhile, Mr Jean-Louis Diefenbacher, Tuan Syed Ahmad Safri
Syed Hussein and Mr Jean-Michel Seillier have been appointed as
director of Intan in place of Mr Robin Tan Yeong Ching and Tengku
Mustaffa Kamel with effect from June 11 1998.
	   Robin Tan will also cease to be executive director with effect
from the same date.
	   Mr Tremain Tanner and Mr Pierre Edovard Brunet are appointed
alternate director to Diefenbacher and Seiller respectively.
	   
</TEXT>
