	   COURTING TROUBLE ... Riding hand-in-hand and at breakneck speed,
these Evel Knievel wannabes throw caution to the wind as they rush
down a main road in Kampung Pelubang in Kubang Pasu district.
Without helmets and only in slippers, these youths braved oncoming
traffic for the thrill of a dangerous stunt.
	   Following them, a group of younger children on bicycles cheered
them, paying scant attention to the sharp bend just a few metres
down the road.
	   New Straits Times photographer Jamah Nasri caught these
daredevils in action on the main road that links Kampung Pelubang
to the Alor Star-Jitra trunk road. The youths rode in this
dangerous manner for 10 minutes.
	   
