AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KOTA BARU, Thurs. - Menteri Besar Datuk Nik Abdul Aziz Nik Mat
has urged agricultural agencies to build close krapport with
farmers to facilitate development in the sector.
	   He said technical support, counselling and new farming methods
could be put into effect if the officers had good ties with
farmers.
	   This would also enable farmers to receive firsthand know-how
from the officers and improve yields.
	   ``The farmers should also be willing to listen to the officers.
	   ``They have to shed the belief that their farming activities are
only for self-sufficiency as this will not help increase food
production,'' he said during his visit to the Kampung Nilam Baru
vegetable farm.
	   Also present was Kemubu Agricultural Development Authority
chairman Tan Sri Hussein Ahmad.
	   Nik Aziz said Kelantan, with its large tracts of land, should be
able to be self-sufficient in vegetables and fruits.
	   However, he said, the State had to import fruits and vegetables
from Thailand. About 36,000 tonnes of fruits and vegetables worth
RM65 million were brought into the State from Thailand every year.
	   ``Between 20 and 30 per cent of this amount is sold in Kelantan
while the rest goes to other States.''
	   Nik Aziz also spoke of the reluctance of many to undertake
farming actively as they had doubts that this could be lucrative.
	   
</TEXT>
