<HEADLINE>
Boy needs RM28,000 for hole-in-the-heart operation, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Boy needs RM28,000 for hole-in-the-heart operation, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Thurs. - The parents of four-month-old Vinoshan
Narayanan are appealing to the public to help them raise RM28,800
for a hole-in-the- heart operation for their only child.
	   Narayanan Pali, 44, of Kampung Pasir Baru, Jalan Kelang Lama, is
a bus driver, earning RM1,200 a month. His wife Sarojini Kanan, 43,
is a housewife.
	   ``My son was born on Feb 6 this year, and I found out about his
heart condition about a month later,'' he said.
	   ``Since then, I have been taking Vinoshan for monthly check ups.
I have used up all my savings on hospital bills.''
	   Vinoshan has been diagnosed as suffering from a
hole-in-the-heart, resulting in congestive heart failure.
	   Narayanan said Vinoshan only drank about three fluid ounces of
milk daily, although four-month-old babies are supposed to drink
between four and six ounces of milk daily.
	   ``He also has difficulty breathing whenever he is fed,'' said
Sarojini. ``I worry because he is underweight; he only weighs
3.7kg.''
	   Vinoshan's operation costing RM28,800 is scheduled to take place
at the Gleneagles Intan Medical Centre as soon as sufficient funds
are collected.
	   He is scheduled to undergo cardiac catheterization and a
surgical closure of the hole-in-the-heart as soon as possible.
	   Those who wish to make donations should make cheques payable to
the New Straits Times and send them to the Cashier's Department,
New Straits Times Press (M) Bhd, 31 Jalan Riong, 59100 Kuala
Lumpur.
	   Donors should also write Vinoshan's name on the reverse side of
the cheque. If a receipt is required, donors should include their
name and address.
	   
</TEXT>
