	   IPOH, Thurs. - An annual commemorative ceremony will be held at
the God's Little Acre in Batu Gajah on Saturday for those who lost
their lives during the communist insurgency.
	   The Perak Planters Association, the organisers, said this year's
ceremony was significant as it marked the 50th anniversary of the
12-year Malayan Emergency which began in 1948.
	   There will be a short service at the Church of the Holy Trinity,
followed by laying of wreath at the cemetery by representatives of
various foreign missions, security forces and organisations.
	   British High Commissioner David Moss and his New Zealand
counterpart Sarah Dennis are expected to lay wreaths on behalf of
their governments.
	   
