<HEADLINE>
Shares up on bargain-hunting, BUSINESS TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Shares up on bargain-hunting, BUSINESS TIMES &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SHARE prices surged in afternoon trade yesterday, fuelled by
bargain hunting amid rumours that the Government would soon reveal
off-budget economic stimulus measures.
	   The Straits Times Industrials index rose 19.02 points or 1.8 per
cent higher to end at 1,086.83. The broader All-Singapore index
slid 1.57 points to close at 305.98.
	   Trading in the morning was largely rangebound, with the further
weakening of regional currencies placing pressure on the stock
market.
	   Turnover rose to 153.777 million shares worth S$282.286 million
from 117.88 million shares valued at S$210.44 million on Wednesday.
Falling shares led those rising, 173 to 106, with 311 issues
unchanged.
	   Heavily traded share was Singapore Telecoms Ltd with 8.5 million
shares traded before falling eight cents to S$2.22. Top gainer was
Singapore Press Holdings Ltd rising S$1.10 to S$12.60 and top loser
was Creative Technology Ltd down S$1.00 to S$26.90.
	   
