	   RED Box (M) Bhd, which is facing a winding-up petition by
Malayan Banking Bhd, said it is still confident that it can meet
all its working capital requirements and sustain its improvement in
group turnover for the current year. In a statement issued to the
Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange, the group said this is despite
operating in an unfavourable business and banking environment where
bank credit facilities are restrictive. ``While we believe that the
operational and financial impact of the winding-up petition on the
group would be minimal, it is important and we will continue to
study alternative debt restructuring and securitisation plans with
a view to settle the matter with Malayan Banking Bhd,'' the group
said. Red Box served notice on June 8 to the solicitors acting for
Malayan Banking Bhd, opposing the petition and applying for it to
be dismissed, it added.
	   
