	   THE Composite Index futures traded on the Kuala Lumpur Options
and Financial Futures tracked the negative note of the cash market
to end lower yesterday.
	   Spot June ended at 481 with 3,546 lots traded while July futures
closed at 478 with 556 lots changing hands.
	   Open interest for June and July stood at 19,996 lots and 2,420
lots respectively.
	   The September and December futures were not traded yesterday and
they settled at 487 and 493 respectively.
	   Dealers said some players sold off their positions in view of
the weak market sentiment following the softer ringgit and the
easier performances of regional stock markets.
	   The ringgit yesterday strenghtened in late trading to close at
3.98 after being dragged to 4.0530 by a weak yen in early trading.
	   
