	   In reference to Rita S. Kalibonso's letter of June 5, our eyes
have been widely opened to the naked truth. No doubt the horrifying
riots were conducted by well-organized and trained people, just
like in a war!
	   The painful result is that people have not only lost their
houses or shops, but also their loved ones. Outrageously, some
women were sexually abused and even worse, some were inhumanely
raped by irresponsible barbarians.
	   It is even more tragic to learn of the suicide of some of the
victims and those threatened with such treatment. Those who did
survive are suffering from such trauma that they are unable to
communicate.
	   We will never be able to turn the clock back to before the
rampage, and we have to hope that our military police and the army
will be able to regroup and accept the challenge to act honorably
and defend the innocent and helpless citizens of this country.
	   Ms. Rita's offer for free consultation aside, I suggest that we
try to raise some funds for the rape victims to help ease their
burden and to show that we CARE!!
	   
</TEXT>
