<SLUG> FEELING-VICTIMIZED sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Feeling victimized, JAKARTA POST
</HEADLINE>
Feeling victimized, JAKARTA POST &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   JAKARTA POST
   INDONESIA
   ENGLISH
   SUMARSONO SASTROWARDOYOASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   One of the characteristics of people who feel victimized is that
they don't want to change. To be called an innocent victim, is
after all very tempting and people feel very comfortable with it.
The signs of feeling victimized are: always feeling right, not
being committed, disliking criticism and an unwillingness to take
risks.
	   A better and more adult reaction would be to take responsibility
by changing their fate, for instance by joining the current reform
movement and taking the risks in stride. The signs of taking
responsibility are: being open to criticism, being committed, a
willingness to admit past mistakes, flexibility, willingness to
take risks and accepting other's opinions.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 JAKARTA POST all rights reserved as distributed
by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
