AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   RAM has reviewed and reaffirmed the long-term rating of
Ornasteel Enterprise Corp (M) Sdn Bhd's guaranteed floating rate
notes (GFRN) at BBB3.
	   The rating reflects the operating environment and financial
profile of Ornasteel Enterprise Corp. It faces fierce competition
with the lack of price regulation and tariff protection for a
majority of their products, coupled with the large number of
international players in the market.
	   Ornasteel has benefited from the weaker ringgit with over 50 per
cent of their sales exported.
	   However, the current market conditions with contracting local
demand have necessitated the need for the company to further expand
their export market.
	   Ornasteel`s first quarter results for 1998 showed an increase in
exports, which if sustainable, may help the company to weather the
current weak demand from its traditional markets.
	   The rating also takes into account the company's exposure to
product dumping by other larger regional players and its
susceptibility to raw material price fluctuations and foreign
exchange risk.
	   However, these risk factors are tempered by the company's
ability to pass off some price increase to customers.
	   RAM said that while the company recorded improved operating
profits for the financial year 1997, lower profit figures are
expected for the current financial year, given the tougher
operating conditions and higher interest cost.
	   However, with no projected capital expansion, Ornasteel`s debt
level is not expected to increase significantly.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 BUSINESS TIMES all rights reserved as distributed
by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
