	   TIMELY Co-Operation wound up his preparations for a comeback win
in the Class 5, Div 6 event over 1200m in the opening race tomorrow
with a splendid workout in Ipoh yesterday.
	   Taken out by jockey Ismadi Ismail, the six-year-old New Zealand
gelding by Epidaurus strode out fluently over the final 600m to
clock 38.8 seconds and had something in reserve at the finish.
	   The going was good.
	   Timely Co-Operation has a win and eight placings in his 35
outings todte. He scored his only success beating Steadfast by 3
1/4 lengths in a Class 5 event over 1700m in Penang in February
last year.
	   Last time out, Timely Co-Operation tried to make all the running
but was beaten into third spot by two-time winner Jasmine in a
Class 5, Div 1 event over 1600m in Ipoh last month in good going.
	   Trained by Washington Leong, Timely Co-Operation looks fighting
fit and should give a good account of himelf this weekend.
	   All fast work was confined to the No 2 grass track and slow work
on the sand track.
