COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   RAM has downgraded the short-term rating of Invescor Ventures
Sdn Bhd's RM20 million revolving underwritten facility (RUF) to NP
from P3(s).
	   The downgrade was due to the slowdown in Invescor's construction
business, compounded with slow collection for construction work
rendered that has caused cash flow problems.
	   As such, its borrowings level increased and rising interest
rates further aggravated the company's liquidity problems.
	   RAM also said the RUF, secured by a 20 per cent stake in
Crescent Hotel Sdn Bhd that can be sold back to Taiping
Consolidated Bhd, does not offer much enhancement to the ratings as
the agency is concerned over Taiping's ability to pay Invescor on a
timely basis.
	   RAM added that Invescor had already exercised its put option
last August 8 but to date has not received the payment from
Taiping.
	   
</TEXT>
