<HEADLINE>
One British soldier, one civilian killed in road accident
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with name of killed British soldier, another wounded &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BANJA LUKA, Bosnia-Herzegovina (AP) _ One British soldier
serving in the NATO-led peace force in Bosnia and one civilian have
been killed and two other people injured in a road accident, the
British forces headquarters announced Friday.
	   According to a press release, the accident occurred Thursday on
Karanovac road, ten kilometers (6.2 miles) south of Banja Luka in
northwestern Bosnia. It involved one peace force vehicle as well as
three civilian cars.
	   The British forces press office later gave the name of killed
soldier as Kevin Bell, 28.
	   Another British soldier in the same vehicle, David Wall, was
injured and is being treated at a NATO hospital in Sipovo, Bosnia.
	   The cause of the accident was not reported.
	   (pvs/kk/as)
</TEXT>
