	   MALAYSIA Airlines' ``Let the Games Begin'' album, dedicated to
all Commonwealth Games '98 athletes, is aimed at lifting the
athletes' spirits to strive for the best, Malaysia Airlines
chairman Tan Sri Tajudin Ramli said.
	   He said it is the airline's contribution in promoting the Games
not only in Malaysia but also at the international level.
	   ``Video clips of songs from the album will be screened on board
all our domestic and international flights to further promote the
Games. We expect to capture the attention of some four million
passengers over the next three months,'' he told reporters in
Petaling Jaya yesterday after the launch of the album by Youth and
Sports Minister Tan Sri Muhyiddin Yassin.
	   He presented a copy of the album to Muhyiddin and Sukom Ninety
Eight executive chairman Gen (R) Tan Sri Hashim Mohd Ali.
	   Tajudin said the album will also be distributed to hotels and
sold at local music stores. The album is available in compact discs
and cassettes, at RM38 and RM15, respectively.
	   The album comprises 10 songs, ranging from moderate ballads and
rhythm and blues to jazz.
	   
