	   CYCLE &AMP; Carriage Bintang Bhd (CCB) announced that it is
currently negotiating terms and conditions of a proposed joint
venture with Mercedes car maker Daimler-Benz of Germany for the
distribution of Mercedes Vito multi-purpose vehicles (MPV) in
Malaysia. In addition, MPV will also be assembled locally by a
third party by the end of next year and in 2002 it would be locally
manufactured, including its engine. CCB also denied statements
stating that Naza Motors Sdn Bhd was given the sole right to bring
in Mercedes SLK into the country. CCB explained that it is the
franchise holder of Mercedes-Benz products in Malaysia and NZ
Wheels Sdn Bhd has been by appointed by CCB as the sole importer of
Mercedes-Benz complete built up vehicles in the country.
	   
