	   THREE-month Klibor futures on the Malaysia Monetary Exchange
(MME) finished sharply lower yesterday in listless trading with
investors taking new short positions in the forward months, dealers
said.
	   Mr Chris Podbury of KAF Apex Futures Sdn Bhd said the declining
trend was seen from the opening session up to the close as sellers
dominated the market. ``However, we expect the three-month Klibor
futures to continue to trade sideways to higher in near term,'' he
added.
	   June 98 was down by seven ticks to 88.95 from Wednesday's close
with 12 lots traded while Sept 98 dropped by 19 ticks to 88.87 with
30 lots traded.
	   Dec 98 eased by 18 ticks to 88.87 with 34 lots traded and March
99 fell by 18 ticks to 88.87 with 30 lots traded.
	   Total open interest stood at 3,245 counters versus 3,172
counters on Wednesday.
	   
