	   TIN price on the Kuala Lumpur Tin Market (KLTM) continued to be
strong, closing the day 39 sen higher at RM24.21 per kg.
	   Dealers said sellers continued to hold on to their stocks as
price remained firm and is expected to rise further.
	   They said overnight price on the London Metal Exchange (LME)
rose US$15.
	   By next week, there is a possibility that it could breach the
RM25 level as there are shortage of supplies and many buyers, a
dealer said.
	   At the opening level, buyers bid for 171 tonnes but sellers
offered only 62 tonnes.
	   Buyers were mainly Europeans and locals.
	   Turnover increased to 77 tonnes from 66 tonnes on Wednesday.
	   The premium commanded by KLTM over LME widened to US$120 from
US$98 on Wednesday.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 BUSINESS TIMES all rights reserved as distributed
