	   MALAYSIAN rubber prices closed lower yesterday on continued lack
of buyers.
	   At the close, July International RSS One dropped one sen to
274.0 sen per kg while SMR 20 shed 2.5 sen to 260 sen per kg.
	   Sentiment has not changed and was also expected to be weak
today, a dealer said.
	   The Inro daily market indicator prices for June 10 fell to
190.03 Malaysian/Singapore cents from 193.66 cents on June 9.
	   The five-day moving average dropped to 195.80 cents from 198.12
cents previously.
	   
