	   MORE foreigners are expected at this year's Sultan Mahmud Bridge
international run in Kuala Terengganu on Aug 9.
	   The run is expected to attract some 4,000 people.
	   ``The bridge run was previously held on a Friday but this year's
has been moved to a Sunday to attract more foreign entries,''
Terengganu Tourism, Arts and Culture Development Committee Chairman
Datuk Ibrahim Awang said.
	   Ibrahim said the 21.1km-run would offer prizes worth about
RM100,000 and was part of the State Government's yearly activities
to develop local sports and tourism.
	   Malaysia's M. Ramachandran and Yvonne Danson of Singapore won
the men's and women's open events respectively last year.
	   The State Government, Petronas, Culture, Arts and Tourism
Ministry, Esso and Permai Park Inn International are this year's
main sponsors for the run which began in 1990. Entries close on
July 20.
	   
