<SLUG> MUNIR-CUP-BOOST sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Munir Cup boost for the game, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Munir Cup boost for the game, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   LTA of Malaysia (LTAM) in a move to liven up the game in the
country, will host the Dato' Munir Cup National Inter-team
championship at Jalan Duta tennis centre in Kuala Lumpur on June
26-28.
	   Shipper's Logistics Management are the main sponsors of the
tournament.
	   They will be come up with RM30,000 and the challenge trophy,
appropriately named after their managing director.
	   ``We are happy to be associated with tennis development in the
country and hope the tournament will help unearth new talents,''
said Munir yesterday.
	   His involvement in tennis has much to do with his wife, Datin
Intan Mahani who is a former national junior champion.
	   She won the junior title in 1986 and went on to play for country
until 1991 but was forced to retire due to a fractured rib.
	   Intan, 28, is also making a return to game and will compete in
the tournament.
	   The tournament is open to State teams, clubs and other
organisations.
	   Each team can field a maximum of eight players.
	   Only one national player is allowed in a team who also have to
register a women player.
	   National players V. Selvam, R. Ramachandran and O. Vasuthevan
have confirmed their participation.
	   The tournament has so far attracted 10 teams and LTAM are
expecting more. Entries close on June 20.
	   
</TEXT>
