<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Laudrup's 100th,0277 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
With Sports-Soccer-Denmark-Saudi Arabia
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; World Cup: Michael Laudrup gets roses and a victory in 100th
international &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LENS, France (AP) _ Michael Laudrup got a huge bunch of roses
and a crucial victory Friday as he made his 100th international
appearance for Denmark.
	   The 33-year-old forward was presented with a bouquet to mark his
century of caps before Denmark kicked off its World Cup finals
campaign against Saudi Arabia at the Stade Felix Bollaert stadium.
	   But after the game, which Denmark won 1-0 on a 68th minute Marc
Rieper header, Laudrup was thinking of the team rather than his
personal milestone.
	   ``This was a great team effort,'' said Laudrup, who will end his
playing career at the end of the World Cup. ``We created a lot of
opportunities but still had trouble capitalizing on our chances.''
	   The man who did capitalize paid tribute to Laudrup's glittering
career.
	   ``I think it is very important for a player to reach 100
internationals,'' Rieper said. ``He has been without doubt the best
player Denmark has ever had. He is a wonderful player and hopefully
the team and him together can do something at this World Cup.''
	   Laudrup ended his club career at Ajax Amsterdam where he helped
the Dutch powerhouse to this season's league and cup double.
	   He also had spells with some of the greatest names in European
soccer _ playing for Real Madrid, Barcelona and Juventus among
others.
	   Laudrup was the only player in the current squad to have played
in Denmark's first World Cup finals appearance in 1986.
	   (mc-rjm)	   
</TEXT>
