	   MALACCA, Thurs. - Zoo Melaka has received good response from
government agencies and the corporate sector for its animal
sponsorship programme.
	   Its public relations officer Masri Arop said to date 45 agencies
and companies had pledged a total of RM117,250 which would be used
to take care of the animals, including feeding them.
	   ``The sponsorship will help ease the zoo's financial burden. We
hope more companies would come forward to sponsor our animals,'' he
said.
	   Masri said Shell Malaysia led the sponsorship contributing
RM20,000 for the care of two white rhinoceroses.
	   The Malacca Municipal Council amd Faxlin Industry Sdn Bhd have
agreed to bear the cost of feeding the giraffes at a cost of
RM10,000.
	   Other sponsors include the Malacca Foundation, the Alor Gajah
District Council, the Jasin District Council, the State Development
Corporation and the Malacca Water Corporation.
	   Masri said Chief Minister Datuk Seri Abu Zahar Isnin was
expected to officially launch the zoo's sponsorship programme on
June 27.
	   
