	   KUALA LUMPUR, Thurs. - The Yang di-Pertuan Agong Tuanku Jaafar
and the Raja Permaisuri Tuanku Najihah today extended their
congratulations to President Fidel Ramos on the occasion of the
Philippines' centennial celebrations of independence tomorrow.
	   The King hopes relations between the two countries will be
further consolidated for the benefit of their people.
	   In a similar message, Prime Minister Datuk Seri Dr Mahathir
Mohamad conveyed his felicitations on the occasion which symbolised
a historic achievement for the Filipino people.
	   Dr Mahathir said the Filipino people's struggle for nationhood
and independence 100 years ago had inspired other people of
Southeast Asia towards achieving similar goals.
	   Foreign Minister Datuk Abdullah Ahmad Badawi will be
representing Malaysia at the centenary celebrations in the
Philippines.
	   Congratulating his counterpart Domingo L. Siazon Jr today,
Abdullah expressed his confidence that friendly relations between
both countries will continue to expand.
	   Wisma Putra in a Press release today said the official events on
the day included the commemoration of the Declaration of the
Philippine Independence, a centennial parade and a gala dinner at
the Malacanang Palace to be hosted by Ramos.
	   Abdullah left for Manila today and will return on Saturday.
	   
</TEXT>
