<HEADLINE>
Lorry attendant acquitted of murder charge, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Lorry attendant acquitted of murder charge, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   IPOH, Thurs. - The High Court today acquitted a lorry attendant
charged with the murder of a watchman without calling for his
defence.
	   P. Manimaran, 32, of Jelapang, was charged with the murder of
Mukang Singh, 70, at Hong Soon Chan Hup Kee godown in Jalan Tun
Perak about 10.30pm on Sept 8, last year.
	   Judge Datuk Kang Hwee Gee, in acquitting him, said the only
evidence before the court was that police had recovered a parang at
his house in Jelapang.
	   ``This piece of evidence alone is insufficient to incriminate
him.''
	   Kang said in any criminal trial the prosecution must prove its
case beyond reasonable doubt, failing which the benefit of the
doubt should be given to an accused person.
	   ``It is better for 100 guilty men to go free than to condemn an
innocent man.''
	   Earlier V.T. Singam, for Manimaran, submitted that the
prosecution had failed to make out a prima facie case against his
client.
	   He said there was no evidence to show that he was found at the
scene of the crime on that day.
	   Singam said police arrested another person in connection with
the crime but he was never produced in court.
	   He posed the question whether that suspect was the murderer.
	   Deputy Public Prosecutor Murtazadi Amran said he left it to the
court as the only evidence of a confession by Manimaran was
dismissed in a trial- within-a-trial.
	   ``We have no other evidence after the confession was ruled as
inadmissible,'' he said.
	   
</TEXT>
