	   JOHOR BARU, Thurs. - The State Government has set up a one-stop
health advice and counselling centre to create awareness on organ
transplants.
	   The Health-Stop, located at the main concourse of the Johor
Tourist Information Centre, is a joint undertaking between the
State Health Department, Women Affairs and Counselling Department,
and Jotic.
	   State Unity, Women Affairs and Social Welfare Committee chairman
Halimah Sadique said the cost of setting up the centre totalled
only RM15,000 as the premises was sponsored by Jotic.
	   ``The staff will promote organ transplants and register those
who are interested in becoming donors. We hope this will correct
the negative views about organ donation and create awareness of its
importance,'' she told reporters after opening the centre
yesterday.
	   The centre is opened daily from 9am to 9pm.
	   
