	   JOHOR BARU, Thurs. - The setting up of a special magistrate's
court to handle Johor Baru City Council's cases has been deferred
to August.
	   This is because the building housing the court, a three-storey
shoplot in Jalan Cenderawasih in Larkin, is to be renovated and
refurbished.
	   The court was originally scheduled to start this month.
	   Datuk Bandar Datuk Hashim Yahaya said the city council had just
called for a tender for the renovation work.
	   
