	   INNER WHEEL KEEPS PUPILS ROLLING ... (From left to right) Amin
Onizukawaki, 10, Chin Jian Seung, 10, Mohd Shahrir Ramli, 12, and
their classmates can now cultivate their musical talents with new
harmonicas, thanks to the Inner Wheel Club of Bangsar.
	   Club president Datin Naresh Kumari (third from left) and
honorary member, Datin Zaiton Palil (fifth from left) presented new
play equipment - a trampoline, easy-walker and the musical
instruments to pupils from the special class of Sekolah Rendah
SS19/6 Subang Jaya.
	   Other club members present were (from left) Daljit Kaur
Pasricha, Jasbir Kaur and Datin Bavanee Samuel.
	   Headmaster Chia Chee Poh, in thanking them, said the gifts would
help the pupils become independent adults.
	   ``Our children need help and support ... a little help goes a
long way,''
	   he said.
	   Zaharah Ismail, coordinating teacher of the class felt happy for
the pupils. ``The new equipment will help with their coordination
and improve their muscular strength,'' she said.
	   Kumari, who read an inspiring poem to guests, added that a
positive approach was vital for the development of the pupils.
	   The pupils were given a hand by the club members in trying out
the latest additions to their classroom.
	   The special class comprising 47 pupils with learning
disabilities are looked after by 13 specially trained teachers.
	   
</TEXT>
