<HEADLINE>
No increase in Negri water rates, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
No increase in Negri water rates, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 12, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SEREMBAN, Thurs. - The Negri Sembilan Government has no
intention of increasing the existing water rates as it does not
want to burden the people, Menteri Besar Tan Sri Mohamad Isa Abdul
Samad said today.
	   ``The last time we revised our water rates was in 1992. We can
revise the rates now but we don't want to do so,'' he said after
witnessing digging work on the first tube-well water project in
Kampung Paroi.
	   He said this was despite the State having to service almost
RM850 million in water infrastructure loans from the Federal
Government.
	   The tube well is capable of supplying 1.12 to 1.8 million litres
of water daily to Taman Tasik Jaya and its neighbouring areas.
	   Three more wells will be dug there soon.
	   A similar project will be carried out in Tanah Merah, Port
Dickson.
	   
</TEXT>
