	   MALACCA, Thurs. - Police have recorded statements from 40 people
who are either relatives or friends of the two men whose bodies
were found in a white Toyota Corolla in Pahang last Tuesday.
	   It is understood that police today recorded statements from the
wife of the man who was found strangled to death.
	   Also interviewed were several policemen and the doctor who
performed the autopsy on the two bodies at the Muadzam Shah
Hospital in Pahang.
	   Police have yet to establish the motive for the killings
although it was earlier said that it could be due to a failed
business transaction.
	   Two Singaporeans were detained at a police roadblock at the
100th km Kuantan-Segamat highway when police found the two bodies
in the car bearing registration number MAF 433.
	   The body found in the boot of the car had a stab wound in the
chest and was wrapped in a blanket, while the other, believed to
have been strangled, was found in the rear seat.
	   Yesterday, State Criminal Investigation Department chief
Assistant Commissioner Mat Zain Ibrahim confirmed that the two
bodies had been claimed by family members on Monday.
	   
