<SLUG> BC-Sports-Golf-European GP, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Spain's Diego Borrego leads rain-shortened European Grand Prix
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: LEADS with conclusion of play &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   SLALEY, England (AP) _ Spain's Diego Borrego shot a 65 to take a
one-stroke lead Friday after the first-round of the rain-delayed
European Grand Prix.
	   Only half of the 156-man field played the round with the other
half schedule to begin play early Saturday in the 650,000-pound
(dlrs 1.06 million) European Tour event.
	   England's Jon Robson, two Swedes _ Mats Hallberg and Pierre
Fulke _ and German Sven Struver shot 66.
	   Officials went to unusual lengths to start things after all play
Thursday was washed out by torrential rain.
	   After waiting until mid-afternoon Friday for the rain to stop,
play was begun with the Slaley Hall course reconfigured to a par-69
instead of the usual par-72.
	   Officials reduced the pars on the 12th, 13th and 18th holes. The
tees on those three were brought forward to assure tee shots would
clear bog-like areas on the fairways.
	   Officials planned to complete the first round Saturday, play the
second later in the day and _ if weather permits _ conclude the
tournament Sunday after only 54 holes.
	   (scw)	   
</TEXT>
