parliament to approve the NATO maneuvers.
	   Macedonia is a member of Partnership for Peace, a group for east
European countries seeking Alliance membership, and its approval
had been expected.
	   Macedonia's prime minister visits Tirana this weekend to discuss
the Kosovo conflict with Albanian counterpart Fatos Nano, who
announced that his Cabinet approved the NATO maneuvers Friday. 	   
