<TEXT>
	   WORLD AT 0000 GMT:
	   NEW:
	   _ALBANIA-RUDDERLESS REBELS. Rebels try to regroup after Serb
offensive.
	   _US-HONG KONG-ECONOMY. Official: former colony to be among first
to rebound.
	   _AUSTRALIA-QUEENSLAND ELECTION. Polls appear too close to call.
	   _UN-ANGOLA. Security Council agrees to freeze foreign-based
funds of UNITA.
	   _US-SHUTTLE-MIR. Space shuttle returns to Earth.
 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia _ Kosovo's ethnic Albanian militants kill
two Serb policemen in one of a series of attacks around the
secessionist province and claim to have mustered a 15,000-strong
fighting force. YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO. Recap expected by 0200 GMT. By
Ismet Hajdari. AP Photos BAJ101-103.
	   ALSO:
	   _YUGOSLAVIA-NATO _ Yugoslavia talks tough to NATO. Expected by
0300 GMT.
	   _ALBANIA-RUDDERLESS REBELS _ Kosovo separatists try to regroup
after Serb offensive. Expected by 0200 GMT.
	   LONDON _ The world's leading industrial nations block new loans
to India and Pakistan in retaliation for their nuclear tests and
impose fresh sanctions on Yugoslavia to protest a wave of ethnic
cleansing in Kosovo. FOREIGN MINISTERS. Has moved. By Edith M.
Lederer.
	   TOKYO _ With the news that Japan is mired in recession, the
world's second-largest economy looks like more of a liability to
its neighbors than a potential savior. JAPAN-RECESSION. Recap
expected by 0100 GMT. By Joji Sakurai. AP Photos
TOK101-103,105-107.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _US-HONG KONG-ECONOMY _ Hong Kong official says former colony to
be among first Asian countries to rebound.
	   LAGOS, Nigeria _ Security forces of Nigeria's latest military
boss send a clear signal to the nation's pro-democracy forces:
Muscle still rules this junta-weary country. NIGERIA. Recap
expected by 0200 GMT. By Tim Sullivan. AP Photos planned.
	   ADIGRAT, Ethiopia _ The guns lay quiet in the Ethiopia-Eritrea
conflict, but the two countries' governments continue their verbal
salvos, blaming each other for the escalating clashes.
ETHIOPIA-ERITREA. Recap expected by 0200 GMT. By Dianna Cahn. AP
Photos ADI101-104.
	   LISBON, Portugal _ Tens of thousands of people flee the former
Portuguese colony of Guinea-Bissau as troops fight renegade
soldiers holed up after a coup attempt, according to media reports.
GUINEA-BISSAU. Recap expected by 0200 GMT. AP Photos
DIK101-103,105-106.
	   BRISBANE, Australia _ As election day dawned Saturday in
Queensland, the headline in the state's biggest newspaper is: ``Too
Close To Call.'' AUSTRALIA-QUEENSLAND ELECTION. Expected by 0600
GMT; polls opened at 2200 GMT Friday, close at 0800 GMT Saturday.
	   ALSO:
	   _AUSTRALIA-HANSON'S HEARTLAND _ This rural community is fertile
ground for the anti-gun control, anti-welfare, anti-Asian
immigration policies of the One Nation Party. Expected by 0800 GMT.
AP Photo BRIS108.
	   DILI, Indonesia _ A dozen political prisoners pardoned by
Indonesia's new president pledge to renew their pro-independence
campaign for East Timor. INDONESIA. Recap expected by 0100 GMT. By
Christopher Torchia. AP Photos JAK101-106.
	   WASHINGTON _ The Chinese ambassador suggests that the United
States needs China as an ally in a region troubled by fresh nuclear
threats and financial crisis. US-CHINA. Has moved. By Laura Myers.
	   UNITED NATIONS _ The Security Council agrees to freeze
foreign-based funds of Angola's UNITA movement and ban the sale of
diamonds by the former rebels effective June 25 unless they meet
terms of a peace agreement. UN-ANGOLA. Has moved. By Robert H.
Reid.
	   NEW DELHI, India _ India claims Pakistan has agreed to resume
top-level talks later this month, but Pakistan's foreign minister
denies it and says India is ``trying to pull a fast one.''
INDIA-PAKISTAN-NUCLEAR. Has moved. By Arthur Max.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _US-PAKISTAN-WHEAT _ U.S. president endorses Pakistan wheat bill
amid Republican criticism.
	   LAS MARGARITAS, Mexico _ With fears of renewed war between
Zapatista rebels and the government, Mexico's president defends his
administration's stated desire for dialogue and to pledge money for
towns where rebel support runs high. MEXICO-CHIAPAS. Has moved. By
Niko Price. AP Photos XSCC101-103.
	   JERUSALEM _ Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu challenges the
position that the Palestinians have accepted a U.S. proposal.
ISRAEL-PALESTINIANS. Has moved. By Jack Katzenell. AP Photo JRL101.
	   BOMBAY, India _ Survivors flee down mud-choked roads in search
of food and drinking water in the aftermath of a cyclone that
killed at least 835 people in western India. INDIA-CYCLONE. Has
moved. By Ramola Talwar. AP Photos BOM101-104,107.
	   CAPE CANAVERAL, Florida _ Space shuttle Discovery returns to
Earth, closing out three years of U.S.-Russian cooperation aboard
the aging space station. US-SHUTTLE-MIR. Recap expected by 0200
GMT. By Marcia Dunn. AP Photos CSB104-107,109-110.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: Queensland state elections in Australia are
Saturday. A two-day European Union summit starts Monday in Cardiff,
Wales.
 &UR; FEATURES:
	   WASHINGTON _ A new exhibit at the U.S. National Gallery of Art,
featuring two painters who are sometimes confused with each other,
puts art lovers and train buffs on the same track.
US-ARTS-MONET-MANET. Has moved. By Carl Hartman. AP Photos
WX102-103.
	    &UR; TRAVEL
	   STOCKHOLM, Sweden _ If the reserved Swedes are usually loath to
call attention to themselves, Stockholmers this year are downright
showing off. Sweden's capital has been designated the 1998 Cultural
Capital of Europe. There will be more than 1,000 events for the
year-long program. TRAV-STOCKHOLM. To move as wire time permits. By
Jim Heintz. AP Photos NY307-NY309.
	   With BC-TRAV-STOCKHOLM-SIDE TRIPS, BC-TRAV-STOCKHOLM-TIPS.
	   LAS VEGAS _ Las Vegas _ once touted as a ``Disneyland for
adults'' _ has spent big bucks to transform itself into a
family-friendly vacation destination. No longer just a cluster of
casinos, Las Vegas today has an array of attractions for all ages.
TRAV-NEW VEGAS. To move as wire time permits. By Robert Macy. AP
Photos NY300-306.
	   With BC-TRAV-NEW VEGAS-ATTRACTIONS, BC-TRAV-NEW VEGAS-TIPS.
	   PORTLAND, Maine _ Oops! There goes the rudder. Thus came to an
end last year's attempt by W. Hodding Carter to sail from Greenland
to Newfoundland in a replica of a Viking ship. But Carter will try
again this summer to reenact Leif Eriksson's 1,500-mile
(2,400-kilometer) voyage. TRAV-VIKING VOYAGE. To move as wire time
permits. By Jerry Harkavy. AP Photo NY310; Graphic TRV VIKING.
	   Also Moving:
	   TRAV-Travel Briefs
