<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAV-New Vegas-Attractions,0677 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
With TRAV-New Vegas
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LAS VEGAS (AP) _ Some of the family attractions in Las Vegas:
	   MIRAGE HOTEL: A 54-foot (16-meter) volcano erupts several times
nightly in front. Free. Dolphin habitat and Secret Garden of
Siegfried and Roy feature rare white lions and tigers raised by the
illusionists. Cost dlrs 10, free for children 10 and under when
accompanied by an adult. Siegfried and Roy stage show features
great illusions and staging, white lions and tigers. At dlrs 89.35,
it's the most expensive show in town, but many believe the best.
	   MGM GRAND HOTEL: Grand Adventures Theme Park features 10 major
attractions, three theaters and six themed areas. Cost dlrs 12 for
11 and older, dlrs 10 for ages 2-10, includes unlimited rides and
shows. Partridge Family sibling David Cassidy stars in ``EFX,'' a
high-energy stage show with outstanding special effects. Cost dlrs
45 and dlrs 63.64; dlrs 31.82 for children 5-12.
	   TREASURE ISLAND HOTEL: Spectacular nightly pirate battles every
90 minutes in front of the resort. No charge. ``Mystere,''
considered the most artistic and challenging show in Las Vegas,
dlrs 69.85 adults, dlrs 34.84 children 12 and under.
	   CIRCUS CIRCUS HOTEL: Pioneer in family entertainment features
carnival midway and Grand Slam Canyon, a domed five-acre
(two-hectare) theme park featuring a roller coaster and numerous
rides and game. Unlimited ride passes from dlrs 11.95 to dlrs
15.95. Children under 33 inches tall admitted free.
	   CAESARS PALACE: Forum Shops at Caesars, billed as the shopping
wonder of the world. Includes Race for Atlantis Imax 3D motion
simulator ride, dlrs 9.50 adults, dlrs 6.75 children. Omnimax
Theater, dlrs 7 admission. Caesars Magical Empire, underground
quality dining with tableside magic, dlrs 60-70.
	   FREMONT STREET EXPERIENCE: Downtown's dlrs 70 million light and
sound extravaganza featuring 2 million lights. Free.
	   FLAMINGO HILTON: ``The Great Radio City Spectacular'' features
the Radio City Rockettes, dinner shows from dlrs 40.87, late show
dlrs 36.32.
	   RIO SUITE HOTEL: ``Masquerade Show in the Sky'' features
elaborate floats and Mardi Gras characters performing nightly.
Free. Popular Danny Gans show, dlrs 60.
	   LAS VEGAS HILTON: Star Trek attraction, features memorabilia
from TV shows and movies, plus 22-minute journey aboard the
Starship Enterprise. Cost dlrs 14.95.
	   SAHARA HOTEL: Sahara Speedworld, virtual reality, three-quarter
scale simulated Indy-style racing, interactive games and two 3-D
theatres. General admission dlrs 3, dlrs 8 for racing.
	   GAMEWORKS: Next to MGM Grand, features more than 250 games of
all types.
	   WORLD OF COCA-COLA - World's largest Coke bottle, theater,
memorabilia museum. dlrs 2, children 5 and under free.
	   STRATOSPHERE HOTEL: 1,149-foot tower topped by two rides, a
roller-coaster encircling the top and the Big Shot, which rockets
riders 160 feet upward from the launch site. Cost dlrs 6 tower,
dlrs 6 Big Shot, dlrs 5 roller coaster.
	   WET 'n WILD _ Water theme park, dlrs 23.95 for ages 10 and
older, dlrs 17.95 ages 3-9, children under 3 free.
	   EXCALIBUR HOTEL: Carnival arcade and King Arthur's Court,
medieval-themed dinner show with jousting knights on horseback.
dlrs 29.95.
	   LUXOR HOTEL: Egyptian-themed interactive attraction, dlrs 6;
Imax 3D Theatre, dlrs 8.50.
	   MONTE CARLO HOTEL: Magician Lance Burton, whose show caters to
families, dlrs 34.95.
	   IMPERIAL PALACE: Legends in Concert features impersonators of
1960s music legends. Price dlrs 29.50, children 12 and under half
price.
	   HOOVER DAM-LAKE MEAD - Popular attraction 27 miles (43
kilometers) southeast of Las Vegas is one the seven engineering
wonders of the world. Free. Tours inside the dam run dlrs 8 for
adults, dlrs 2 for children 6-16, 5 and under free.
	   LAS VEGAS MOTOR SPEEDWAY - Open year-round with more than 20
race tracks featuring events ranging from NASCAR to hot rods.
</TEXT>
