</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAV-New Vegas-Tips,0441 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
With TRAV-New Vegas
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By The Associated Press &QC; 

<TEXT>
	    &UR; IF YOU GO ...
	    &UR; ROOM RATES: Lowest rates run mid-week, highest on the weekend.
On the high end, Caesars Palace, dlrs 109 to dlrs 279 for standard
rooms, The Mirage dlrs 79 to dlrs 159. Circus Circus dlrs 29 to
dlrs 89. All rates subject to availability; higher on major
holidays and during major conventions.
	    &UR; TRANSPORTATION: McCarran International Airport is an dlrs 8-
dlrs 15 taxi ride from the Strip; dlrs 15- dlrs 17 to the downtown
area. Vans go from the airport to various hotels. Numerous rental
car agencies at the airport. The Las Vegas Strip is about three
miles (4.8 kilometers) long and you can walk to and from many major
hotels. Some hotels also offer free shuttle buses between various
points. There is a free monorail covering the 1-mile
(1.6-kilometer) stretch between the MGM Grand and Bally's
hotel-casinos. In addition, a public bus system runs between
downtown and the Strip.
	    &UR; TOUR PACKAGES: Most travel agencies work with a host of tour
wholesalers who offer Las Vegas packages that include rooms, air
fare and ground transportation.
	    &UR; WEATHER: It may be hot, but it's a dry heat. Well, sort of.
Summer highs tend to park around the century mark, sometimes
reaching 110. Overnight lows are generally in the 70s and 80s. The
good news is that many days find the humidity in the single digit
range, more often 10 to 20 percent.
	    &UR; DRESS: Casual. Although you'll see some suits and cocktail
dresses at the major shows, the dress code has relaxed markedly
from the days when elegance was in. Locals dress for the hot
weather and visitors are learning to do the same. Don't forget the
swimwear and sunscreen.
	    &UR; MEALS: Leave the calorie counter behind. The city is famous for
its buffets, which range from dlrs 1.95 to dlrs 3.95 for breakfast,
dlrs 4.95 to dlrs 10.95 for dinner. Food prices are very reasonable
and many hotels offer ``graveyard specials'' such as steak and eggs
for around dlrs 1.95 to lure customers into the casinos after 11
p.m.
	    &UR; AIRLINES: Airlines serving Las Vegas include Southwest, America
West, United, Delta, American, Continental, Reno Air, Northwest.
Alaska, TWA, US Air, Hawaiian, Frontier, Midwest Express and
Midway. The city is also serviced by 14 air charter companies.
	    &UR; INFORMATION: The Las Vegas Convention and Visitors Authority
can provide additional information. Write LVCVA, Las Vegas
Convention Center, 3150 Paradise Road, Las Vegas, NV. 89109-9096,
Attn: Visitor Center. Phone (702) 892-7575. Web address:
LASVEGAS24HOURS.COM.
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-TRAV-New Vegas-Tips; CT:i; 
