<SLUG> BC-Argentina-Airport Fire,0107 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Fire at Argentine airport plays havoc with flights
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) _ A small fire at the capital's
international airport played havoc with flights at the Buenos Aires
airport, authorities said.
	   There were no reports of injuries from the fire, which was
detected Friday afternoon and put out by firefighters in a complex
that also houses the air controller's tower, authorities said.
	   The fire disrupted operations and scrambled flight schedules,
complicating travel plans for many ahead of a three-day holiday
weekend in Argentina, which concludes Monday with Flag Day.
